function ensure(fn) {
    return fn;
    return function() {
        try {
            return(fn.apply(this, arguments));
        } catch(e) {
            if(window.console &amp;&amp; console.error) console.error("Reporting: "+e);
            Raven.captureException(e);
            // throw e;
        }
    };
}

$ensure = function(f){
    return jQuery(ensure(f));
};

  <script type="text/javascript">
   function hum(s){
        if(s&gt;=1048576) return ((s/1048576)|0) + ' MB';
        if(s&gt;=1024) return ((s/1024)|0) + ' KB';
        return s+' bytes'
    }
    var maSpeed = 0;
    var maSpeed2 = 0;
    var lastLoaded = 0;
    updateStats = ensure(function(){
        var pl = [];
        var sss = 0;
        var ttt = 0;
        var loaded = 0;
        for(i in videoplayers){
            var iv = videoplayers[i].players;
            for(j in iv){
                try{
                    iv[j].div.css('top', '0px');
                    var jv = iv[j].player.ytplayer;
                    var s = jv.getVideoBytesLoaded();
                    var t = jv.getVideoBytesTotal();
                    if(t){
                        pl.push(jv);
                        if(s == t) loaded ++;
                        sss += s;
                        ttt += t;
                    }
                }catch(e){
                }
            }
        }
        var percent = (sss+0.001)*100/(ttt+0.001);
        var diff = (sss-lastLoaded) * 4;
        lastLoaded = sss;
        maSpeed = maSpeed * 0.95 + (diff&lt;0?0:diff) * 0.05;
        maSpeed2 = maSpeed2 * 0.995 + (diff&lt;0?0:diff) * 0.005;
        if(sss == ttt) maSpeed = 0;
        if(maSpeed&lt;0) maSpeed = 0;
        if(maSpeed2&lt;0) maSpeed2 = 0;
        var eta = (ttt-sss)/(maSpeed2+0.001);
        if(eta &gt; 86400) eta = 'never';
        else if(eta &gt; 3600) eta = ((eta/3600)|0)+' hours';
        else if(eta &gt; 60) eta = ((eta/60)|0)+' minutes';
        else eta = (eta|0)+' seconds';
        $('.videoload').html("&lt;span&gt;players:&lt;/span&gt; "+loaded+' of '+pl.length+" loaded&lt;br/&gt;"+hum(sss)+" of "+hum(ttt)+"&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;loaded:&lt;/span&gt; "+(percent|0)+"%&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span&gt;loading:&lt;/span &gt;"+hum(maSpeed|0)+"/sec&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span&gt;ETA:&lt;/span&gt; "+eta);
    });
    function init_videoload(){
        if(!window.videoload){
            window.videoload = true;
            for(i in videoplayers){
                videoplayers[i].setMultiplePlayers(true);
            }
            $ensure(function(){
                setInterval(updateStats, 250);
            });
        }
    }
  </script>

        }

            }
        }

  <script type="text/javascript">
   &lt;!--
    var showBooksDone = false;
    showBooks = ensure(function(){
        if(!showBooksDone) showBooksDone = true;
        else return;
        var query = 'night sky';
        function esc(x){ return x.replace(/[ \"%:;_@#$&amp;{}&lt;&gt;]+/g, '_');}
        var itemTemplate = _.template('&lt;li class="border_color opacity font_color shadow"&gt;'+
            '&lt;div class="img_container"&gt;&lt;a href="&lt;%= url %&gt;"&gt;&lt;img src="&lt;%= img %&gt;"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;'+
            '&lt;div class="title bgr_color"&gt;&lt;a href="&lt;%= url %&gt;"&gt;&lt;%= title %&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;'+
            '&lt;div class="authors bgr_color"&gt;&lt;span data-trans="Authors:"&gt;Authors:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;%= authors %&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;');
        var target = jQuery('#books ul.book');
        jQuery.ajax({
            url: 'https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes?q='+query,
            dataType: 'jsonp',
            success: ensure(function(r){
                target.find('li').detach();
                var records = {'query': query};
                for(var i in r.items){
                    var vi = r.items[i].volumeInfo;
                    if(vi.authors == null) continue;
                    if(vi.imageLinks == null){
                        vi.imageLinks = {};
                    }
                    records['id'+i] = r.items[i].id;
                    records['authors'+i] = vi.authors.join('|');
                    records['title'+i] = vi.title
                    records['subtitle'+i] = vi.subtitle || '';
                    records['img'+i] = vi.imageLinks.thumbnail;
                    var title = vi.title;
                    var name = vi.title;
                    if(vi.subtitle){
                        title = title + ': ' + vi.subtitle;
                        name = name + '-' + vi.subtitle;
                    }
                    var authorLinks = [];
                    jQuery.each(vi.authors, function(i,a){
                        authorLinks.push('&lt;a href="http://wn.com/'+esc(a)+'"&gt;'+a+'&lt;/a&gt;')
                    });
                    var ctx = {
                        id: r.items[i].id,
                        url: 'http://wn.com/'+esc(vi.authors[0]+'-'+name)+'/#/book',
                        img: vi.imageLinks.thumbnail,
                        title: title,
                        authors: authorLinks.join(', '),
                    };
                    var text = itemTemplate(ctx);
                    target.append(text);
                }
                jQuery.ajax({
                   url: 'http://my.wn.com/bookcache/',
                   type: 'GET',
                   dataType: 'script',
                   data: records
                });
            })
        });
    });
    // --&gt;

  <script type="text/javascript">
   &lt;!--
    var ALTERNATE_CSS_BASE='http://cdn0.wn.com/or/ula/cheetah-photo-search/2012-10-08/';
    var styleOverride = null;
            var days = 365;
        function setCookie(cookieName, value) {
            var expiryDate = new Date();
            expiryDate.setTime(expiryDate.getTime()+(days * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000));

            jQuery.cookies.set(cookieName, value, {
                expiresAt: expiryDate
            });
        }

        var wnstyle_cookie = 'wnstyle';
        var bgcolor=false;
        var linkcolor=false;

        window.switchStyle = function(styleName, dontSave) {
            if(!jQuery(".themeswitch#"+styleName).length){
                styleName = 'white';
            }
            //jQuery('#videoquery0').val(jQuery('#videoquery0').val()+styleName+' ');
            var activeStylesheetIndex = -1;
            var activeStylesheet = null;
            var newActiveStylesheet = null;
            jQuery('link[title]').each(
                function(i)
                {
                  if(this.getAttribute('rel').match('style')){
                    if (this.getAttribute('title') == styleName) {
                        this.disabled = false;
                        activeStylesheetIndex = i;
                        newActiveStylesheet = this;
                    }else{
                        if(!this.disabled &amp;&amp; !activeStylesheet){
                            activeStylesheet = this;
                        }else{
                            this.disabled = true;
                        }
                    }
                  }
                }
            );
            if(activeStylesheetIndex == -1){
                //jQuery('link[@rel*=style][title=white]')[0].disabled=false;
                newActiveStylesheet = document.createElement("link");
                newActiveStylesheet.rel = 'stylesheet alternate';
                newActiveStylesheet.type = "text/css";
                newActiveStylesheet.title = styleName;
                newActiveStylesheet.href = ALTERNATE_CSS_BASE+styleName+'.css';
                newActiveStylesheet = document.getElementsByTagName("head")[0].appendChild(newActiveStylesheet);
                newActiveStylesheet.disabled=true;
                if(activeStylesheet){
                    activeStylesheet.disabled=true;
                }
                newActiveStylesheet.disabled=false;
                setTimeout(function () { // repeat if style didn't load
                    newActiveStylesheet.disabled=true;
                    if(activeStylesheet){
                        activeStylesheet.disabled=true;
                    }
                    newActiveStylesheet.disabled=false;
                }, 500);
            }else if(activeStylesheet &amp;&amp; activeStylesheet.getAttribute('title') != styleName){
                newActiveStylesheet.disabled = true;
                activeStylesheet.disabled=true;
                newActiveStylesheet.disabled = false;
                // setTimeout(function () {
                //     newActiveStylesheet.disabled = false;
                // }, 100);
            }
            var bgstyle = 'transparent';
            var styleImage = jQuery.cookies.get('wnskin');
            if(styleImage){
                bgstyle = 'url(http://login.wn.com/media/skins/'+styleImage+')';
            }
            jQuery(".custom_bgr").css({'background' : bgstyle});
            if(!dontSave){
                setCookie(wnstyle_cookie, styleName);
            }
            $('#skins').trigger('skin.changed', [styleName, styleImage]);
        };

    jQuery(function() {
            if(styleOverride){
                switchStyle(styleOverride, true);
            }else{
                var style = jQuery.cookies.get(wnstyle_cookie);
                if (style) {
                    switchStyle(style);
                }
            }

            // legacy code support: updating default colors from cookies
            if (jQuery.cookies.get('linkcolor')) { linkcolor = jQuery.cookies.get('linkcolor');}
            else { linkcolor = 'ffffff'; }
            if (jQuery.cookies.get('bgcolor')) { bgcolor = jQuery.cookies.get('bgcolor');}
            else { bgcolor = '000000'; }
            jQuery('#color-link div').css('backgroundColor', '#' + linkcolor);
            jQuery('#color-bg div').css('backgroundColor', '#' + bgcolor);

            jQuery('.themeswitch').click(function(event) {
                event.preventDefault();
                var style = jQuery(this).attr('id');
                switchStyle(style);
            });

    });

    // --&gt;
  </script>

  <script async="true" defer="true" nopack="1" src="http://assets.wn.com/media/ling/anything-events.js" type="text/javascript">

  <script type="text/javascript">
   /* wrs: attempt to track how long people stay on the page by logging an event every 15 seconds */
  var wrs_page_load_time = new Date().getTime();
  var wrs_last_log_time = 0;
  var wrs_log_interval = 30;

  function wrs_log_time_on_page()
  {
      /* calculate time on page, fudge it up a little in case event fires early, then round down to nearest 15 seconds */
      var wrs_time_on_page = 1 + ((new Date().getTime() - wrs_page_load_time) / 1000);
      wrs_time_on_page = wrs_time_on_page - (wrs_time_on_page % 15);

      if(wrs_time_on_page &lt; 180 || (wrs_time_on_page - wrs_last_log_time) &gt; wrs_log_interval){
          wrs_last_log_time = wrs_time_on_page;
          if(wrs_time_on_page &gt; 600)
              wrs_log_interval = 120;
          if(wrs_time_on_page &gt; 2400)
              wrs_log_interval = 300;
          _gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'WNAnything', 'StillOnPage', wrs_time_on_page.toFixed()]);
      }
  }

  setInterval(wrs_log_time_on_page, 15000);
  </script>

        window.page_query = 'night sky';
        update_user_actions = ensure(function(data){
                if(data.username){
                    $('#login').html(data.html);
                    window.username = data.username;
                }
                $ensure(function(){
                    if(data.editable){ // user is owner
                        $('.signup-box').html('&lt;a id="id_save_playlist"  class="sign_up" onclick="return save_playlist(this.href)" href="http://editor.wn.com/save_playlist/night_sky/"&gt;&lt;span data-trans="Save playlist"&gt;Save playlist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;');
                        $('.button').html('&lt;a id="id_save_playlist"  class="sign_up" onclick="return save_playlist(this.href)" style="float: none !important;" href="http://editor.wn.com/save_playlist/night_sky/"&gt;&lt;span data-trans="Save this page"&gt;Save this page&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;');
                    }else if(data.username){ // watching other user page
                        $('.signup-box').html('&lt;a onclick="return login_and_save_playlist(\'http://editor.wn.com/save_playlist/night_sky/\', this.href)" rel="nofollow" class="sign_up" href="http://editor.wn.com/fork/wn/night_sky/"&gt;&lt;span data-trans="Save playlist"&gt;Save playlist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;');
                        $('.button').html('&lt;a onclick="return login_and_save_playlist(\'http://editor.wn.com/save_playlist/night_sky/\', this.href)" rel="nofollow" class="sign_up" style="float: none !important;" href="http://editor.wn.com/fork/wn/night_sky/"&gt;&lt;span data-trans="Save this page"&gt;Save this page&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;');
                    }
                    if(data.username){
                        $('.not_editable').hide();
                        $('.is_editable').show();
                    }else{
                        $('.not_editable').show();
                        $('.is_editable').hide();
                    }
                });
        });

        query_user_actions = ensure(function(){
            jQuery.ajax({
                data: {
                    edit: 'night_sky',
                    owner: 'wn',
                    ieditor: 'http://editor.wn.com',
                },
                dataType: 'jsonp',
                url: 'http://login.wn.com/actions/i/',
                success: function(data) {
                    update_user_actions(data);
                },
            });
        });
        query_user_actions();
        // --&gt;

   <!-- SET LYRICS ARTISTS NAME -->
   <script type="text/javascript">
    function load_wiki(el, cb) {
        var el = $(el).closest('.wiki-page').find('.wikiparser');
        var query = el.data('title');
        var main = el.data('main');
        var custom = el.data('custom');
        var onSuccess = function(){
            wikisnippet.hide();
            updateHeight();
            if(cb) cb();
        };
        if(custom) {
            onSuccess();
        }else{
            var wikisnippet = el.find('.wikisnippet');
            el.find('.wikipage a').html('Loading... please wait...');
            el.closest('div').load('/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/wiki_page?main='+main+'&amp;query='+escape(query), onSuccess);
        }
        return false;
    }
    function load_playlistlyrics(query) {
        var lyrics_query = query.replace('&amp;', ' ').replace('[', ' ').replace(']', '').replace('@', ' ').replace('live', ' ').replace('Live', ' ').replace('(', ' ').replace(')', ' ').replace('"', ' ').replace('!', ' ')
        jQuery.ajax({
            url: '/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/lyrics_playlist',
            data: {'query': lyrics_query,
                   'artist': 'Night sky'
            },
            dataType: 'text',
            success: ensure(function(text) {
                text = text.trim().split(new RegExp("&lt;"+"!--"),1)[0];
                if(!text) {
                    var song = "";
                }else{
                    var matches = text.trim().match(new RegExp("(.*)\n(.*)\n([^]*)"));
                    var song = matches[3];
                    jQuery('.lyrics_icon').show();
                    jQuery('.lyrics_body').html(song);
                }
            })
        });
        return false;
    }
   </script>

                '&lt;div class="content"&gt;&lt;a class="playlistitem" id="&lt;%= id %&gt;_line" href="#"&gt;'+
                '&lt;div class="video-thumb border_color bgr_color descriptions-tab-thumbnail gotop"&gt;'+
                '&lt;img class="video-thumbnail gotop playvideo1"  onClick="activateTab(\'playlist1\'); return false" width="300" height="225" alt="&lt;%= title %&gt;" src="&lt;%= thumbnailUrl %&gt;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;'+
                '&lt;div class="video-title" &gt;'+
                '&lt;a class="playlistitem playvideo1 gotop"  onClick="activateTab(\'playlist1\'); return false" id="&lt;%= id %&gt;_more" href="#"&gt;&lt;%= title %&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;'+
                '&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-trans="Order:"&gt;Order:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;input type="text" size="2" value="&lt;%= order %&gt;" class="details-manual-order" /&gt;'+
                '&lt;a href="javascript:void(0);" class="details-manual-order-confirm" style="display:none;" title="Move to new position" data-title="Move to new position"&gt;&lt;span data-trans="Reorder"&gt;Reorder&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;'+

                    videoplayers[vsid].playPlaylist();
            });

            jQuery(document).keyup(ensure(function(e) {
                if (e.keyCode == 27) {
                    jQuery('#home'+vsid+'').click();
                    return false;
                }
            }));

    });

   <script type="text/javascript">
    &lt;!--
        //jQuery(function() {
        window.bind_video_details = ensure(function(vsid){
            var target = $('#details'+vsid+' .center-content');
            videoplayers[vsid].playerContainer.bind('videoplayer.player.playlistchanged', function(e, playlist){
                target.find('.video-desc').detach();
                for(var i in playlist){
                    var item = playlist[i];
                    var itemId = _.uniqueId('item_');
                    var context = {
                        descriptionsholder: '#descriptionsplace'+vsid+'',
                        id: itemId,
                        info: "{source: '"+item.source+"', video_id: '"+item.video_id+"', duration: "+item.duration+", published: '"+item.published+"', updated: '"+item.updated+"', author: ''}",
                        url: item.title.replace(/ /g, '_').replace(/"/g,'&quot;')+'/video_details',
                        title: item.title,
                        titled: item.title+'/video details',
                        durationStr: videoplayers[vsid].formatTime(item.duration),
                        description: item.description,
                        updated: item.updated,
                        author: item.author,
                        published: item.published,
                        order: (+i)+1,
                        thumbnailUrl: item.thumbnailUrl,
                        tooltipContentBody: item.tooltipContentBody,
                    };
                    var item_text = detailsTemplate(context);
                    target.append(item_text);
                }
            });

                    // getting the video details delete button to work
                    $('#details'+vsid+' .video-remove').live('click', function(e) {
                        var toRemove = videoplayers[vsid].extractVideoData(this);
                        var playlist = videoplayers[vsid].getPlaylist();
                        for (var i = 0; i &lt; playlist.length; i++) {
                            var playlistItem = playlist[i];
                            if(videoplayers[vsid].isSameVideo(playlistItem, toRemove)){
                                playlist.splice(i--, 1);
                            }
                        }
                        videoplayers[vsid].setPlaylist(playlist);
                        $(this).parent('div.video-desc').detach();
                        var items = $('#details'+vsid+' .video-desc .details-manual-order');
                        for (var i = 0; i &lt; items.length; i++) {
                            $(items[i]).val(i+1);
                        }

                    });
                    $('#details'+vsid+' .descriptions-tab-thumbnail').click(function(event) {//
                            activateTab('playlist'+vsid+'');
                     });
                    // ordering logic
                    var pl_len = $('#details'+vsid+' .video-desc').length;
                    var init_vlist_value = false;
                    var new_vlist_value = false;
                    $('#details'+vsid+' .details-manual-order').live('hover', function(e) {
                        $(this).select();
                        if (!init_vlist_value) { init_vlist_value = parseInt($(this).val()); }
                    });
                    $('#details'+vsid+' .details-manual-order').live('focus', function(e) {
                        if (!init_vlist_value) { init_vlist_value = parseInt($(this).val()); }
                    });
                        //$('#details'+vsid+' .details-manual-order').blur(function(e) {
                        //  $(this).parent().find('.details-manual-order-confirm').hide();
                        //})
                    $('#details'+vsid+' .details-manual-order').live('keyup',function(e) {
							alert('test');
                            $(this).parent().find('.details-manual-order-confirm').hide();
                            new_vlist_value = parseInt($(this).val());
                            if (isNaN(new_vlist_value)) { return false; }
                            if (new_vlist_value == undefined) { return false; }
                            if (new_vlist_value == parseInt(init_vlist_value)) { return false; }
                            if (new_vlist_value &lt; 0) { return false; }
                            if (new_vlist_value &gt; pl_len) { return false; }
                            if (new_vlist_value == 0) { new_vlist_value = 1; }
                            $(this).parent().find('.details-manual-order-confirm').show();
                    });
                        // add the keypress event
                        $('#details'+vsid+' .details-manual-order').live('keypress', function(e) {
                            if(e.keyCode == 13) {
                                var tmp = $('#details'+vsid+' .video-desc').eq(init_vlist_value-1);
                                var target = $('#details'+vsid+' .video-desc').eq(new_vlist_value-1);
                                var tmpc = tmp.clone(true);

                                target.find('.details-manual-order').val(init_vlist_value);
                                tmp.replaceWith(target);
                                var place = $('#details'+vsid+' .video-desc').eq(new_vlist_value-1);
                                tmpc.insertBefore(place);

                                var items = $('#details'+vsid+' .video-desc .details-manual-order');
                                for (var i = 0; i &lt; items.length; i++) {
                                    $(items[i]).val(i+1);
                                }

                                videoplayers[vsid].switchPlaylistItems(init_vlist_value, new_vlist_value);
                                init_vlist_value = false;
                                new_vlist_value = false;
                                $('#details'+vsid+' .details-manual-order-confirm').hide();
                            }
                        });

                        $('#details'+vsid+'-items .details-manual-order-confirm').live('click', function(e) {
                                tmp = $('#details'+vsid+' .video-desc').eq(init_vlist_value-1);
                                target = $('#details'+vsid+' .video-desc').eq(new_vlist_value-1);
                                tmpc = tmp.clone(true);

                                target.find('.details-manual-order').val(init_vlist_value);
                                tmp.replaceWith(target);
                                place = $('#details'+vsid+' .video-desc').eq(new_vlist_value-1);
                                tmpc.insertBefore(place);

                                var items = $('#details'+vsid+' .video-desc .details-manual-order');
                                for (var i = 0; i &lt; items.length; i++) {
                                    $(items[i]).val(i+1);
                                }

                                videoplayers[vsid].switchPlaylistItems(init_vlist_value, new_vlist_value);
                                init_vlist_value = false;
                                new_vlist_value = false;
                                $('#details'+vsid+' .details-manual-order-confirm').hide();
                        });

                $('#playlistformating'+vsid+'').hover(function() {
                            $('.playlistformating.fsmode').stop(true, false).animate({'right': '0px'}, 900);
                            $('.playlistformating.fsmode').css("background-image", "url(http://cdn3.wn.com/or/images/double-right-arrow.png)");
                        }, function() {
                            $('.playlistformating.fsmode').stop(true, false).animate({'right': '-365px'}, 900);
                            $('.playlistformating.fsmode').css("background-image", "url(http://cdn8.wn.com/or/images/double-left-arrow.png)");

                });


        });
        // --&gt;
   </script>
   <script type="text/javascript">
    var remove_dynamic_playlist = ensure(function(num){
    var target_li = $('#playlist_menu');
    target_li.find('.remove-'+num).parent().remove();
    var first_playlist = target_li.find('a').attr('id');
    if(first_playlist){
        $("#main-menu li[id='#playlist_menu'] a").attr('id', first_playlist);
    }

    var target_li = $('#details_menu');
    target_li.find('.remove-'+num).parent().remove();
    var first_details = target_li.find('a').attr('id');
    if(first_details){
        $("#main-menu li[id='#details_menu'] a").attr('id', first_details);
    }
    var target_pl = $('#tabcontainer');
    target_pl.find('#playlist'+num).remove();
    target_pl.find('#details'+num).remove();
});
   </script>
   <script type="text/javascript">
    var found_playlists = null;
var longest_position = 0;
var add_cached_videos = ensure(function(count){
    if(!count) { count = 1; }
    if(!found_playlists){ return; }
    if(count&gt;found_playlists.length){
        count = found_playlists.length;
    }
    if(!found_playlists.length){
        $('.add_youtube_playlist').hide();
        // _add_dynamic_playlist('night sky', 'no more playlists');
        return;
    }
    for(var i=0; i&lt;+count; i++){
        var p = found_playlists.splice(0, 1);
        if(p.length){
            p = p[0];
            var activate = (i == count-1);
            _add_dynamic_playlist('playlist:'+p.playlist_id, p.title, (i == count-1)? activate_playlist : function(){});
        }
    }
});

function activate_playlist(status, num){
    if(status == 'loading'){
        activateTab('playlist'+num);
        $('#id_new_playlist').attr('value', '');
    }
}

var show_loading = ensure(function(status){
    if(status){
        // add class "loading" to loading button
    }else{
        // remove class "loading" to loading button
    }
})

var add_longest_videos = ensure(function(){
    var q = 'night sky';
    var num = ++longest_position;
    _add_dynamic_playlist(q+' duration:longest', q + ' longest #'+num, activate_playlist, num*14);
});

var add_more_videos = ensure(function(count){
    if(!count) { count = 1; }
    if(found_playlists){
        add_cached_videos(count);
        $('.single-playlist-fullscreen').hide();
    }else{
        found_playlists = [];
        show_loading(true);
        $('.single-playlist-fullscreen').hide();
        $.ajax({
            url: 'http://wn.com/api/upge/edit/find_playlists',
            data: {query: 'night sky'},
            dataType: 'jsonp',
            success: ensure(function(response){
                show_loading(false);
                found_playlists = response['results'];
                if(found_playlists){
                    add_cached_videos(count);
                }
            }),
            failure: ensure(function() {
                show_loading(false);
            })
        });
    }
});

var tab_num = null;

var _add_playlist = ensure(function(loader, query, title, callback, offset, autostart){
    if(!title){
        title = query;
    }
    show_loading(true);
    if(!tab_num){
        tab_num = $('#playlist_menu li').length;
    }
    $('#playlist_menu').show(); // in case there were zero videos
    var num = ++tab_num;

    //add videos
    var target_li = $('#playlist_menu');
    var code_li = _.template('&lt;li class=""&gt;&lt;div id="v-remove-&lt;%= num %&gt;" class="remove remove-&lt;%= num %&gt;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;a href="" id="#playlist&lt;%= num %&gt;" '+
            'class="playlist-menu-&lt;%= num %&gt;"&gt;&lt;%= title %&gt;&lt;/a&gt;'+
            '&lt;div onclick="return triggerFullscreen(&lt;%= num %&gt;);" class="fullscreen rounded glow"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;');
    target_li.append(code_li({num: num, title: title}));

    var target_pl = $('#tabcontainer');
    var code_pl = _.template('&lt;div id="playlist&lt;%= num %&gt;" class="playlist-page" style="display: block; position: absolute; margin-left: -10000px; max-width: 9000px"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;');
    target_pl.append(code_pl({num: num}));

    // add video details
    var target_li = $('#details_menu');
    var code_li = _.template('&lt;li class=""&gt;&lt;div id="d-remove-&lt;%= num %&gt;" class="remove remove-&lt;%= num %&gt;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;a href="" id="#details&lt;%= num %&gt;" '+
            'class="details-menu-&lt;%= num %&gt;"&gt;&lt;%= title %&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;');
    target_li.append(code_li({num: num, title: title}));

    var target_pl = $('#tabcontainer');
    var code_pl = _.template('&lt;div id="details&lt;%= num %&gt;" class="details-page" style="display: block; position: absolute; margin-left: -10000px; max-width: 9000px"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;');
    target_pl.append(code_pl({num: num}));

    loader(num, query, title, callback, offset, autostart);

    callback('loading', num);
    $('.single-playlist-fullscreen').hide();

    return false;
});

var _add_dynamic_playlist = ensure(function(query, title, callback, offset, autostart){
  return _add_playlist(function(num, query, title, callback, offset, autostart){
     jQuery.ajax({
        url: 'http://wn.com/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/dynamic_playlist_v2',
        data: {
           language_id: '1',
           vsid: num,
           query: query,
           offset: offset|0
        },
        dataType: 'jsonp',
        success: ensure(function(response) {
            jQuery('#playlist'+num).html(response['videos']);
            jQuery('#details'+num).html(response['video_details']);
            bind_videos(num, autostart);
            bind_video_details(num);
            $('#playlist'+num).css('display', 'block');
            // $('.tabtrigger li a[id=#playlist'+num+']').first().click();
            // activateTab('playlist'+num);
            updateHeight();
            show_loading(false);
            callback('loaded', num);
        }),
        failure: ensure(function() {
            show_loading(false);
            callback('failed', num);
        })
    })}, query, title, callback, offset, autostart);
});

var add_dynamic_playlist = ensure(function(query, title){
    _add_dynamic_playlist(query, title, activate_playlist);
});

var _video_importer = function(num, query, title, callback, offset, autostart){
     jQuery.ajax({
        url: 'http://manage.wn.com/api/collect_videos',
        data: {
           urls: query.trim().replace(/\r*\n\r*/g,'|'),
        },
        dataType: 'jsonp',
        success: ensure(function(response) {
            jQuery('#playlist'+num).html($('#playlist0').html().replace(/0"/g, num+'"'));
            jQuery('#details'+num).html($('#details0').html().replace(/0"/g, num+'"'));
            bind_videos(num, autostart);
            bind_video_details(num);
            clog(response.results);
            var vp = videoplayers[num];
            var playlist = [];
            _.each(response.results, function(el) {
                var data = {
                    source: 'youtube',
                    video_id: el.youtube_video_id,
                    author: el.author_name,
                    duration: el.duration_seconds,
                    title: el.title,
                    published: new Date(el.published).toDateString(),
                    updated: new Date(el.updated).toDateString(),
                    video_views: el.view_count,
                    thumbnailUrl: el.thumbnail_url.replace('/default.jpg', '/0.jpg'),
                    tooltipContentBody: el.description,
                    description: el.description,
                };
                playlist.push(data);
            });
            vp.setPlaylist(playlist);
            vp.loadPlaylist(autostart);
            $('#playlist'+num).css('display', 'block');
            // $('.tabtrigger li a[id=#playlist'+num+']').first().click();
            // activateTab('playlist'+num);
            updateHeight();
            show_loading(false);
            callback('loaded', num);
        }),
        failure: ensure(function() {
            show_loading(false);
            callback('failed', num);
        })
    })}

var import_videos = ensure(function(query){
  return _add_playlist(_video_importer, query, 'Imported videos', activate_playlist, 0, true);
});

var do_import = ensure(function(el){
  var query = $(el).parent().find('textarea').val();
  $.unblockUI();
  return import_videos(query);
});


var start_import = ensure(function(){
    var w = $('body').width();
    $.blockUI({
        message: 'Enter keywords in the box below, one query per line; they could be names, places, phraseswhatever you are interested in, i.e. "funny cats" or "bicycle tricks".&lt;br&gt;' +
                 'You can choose specific videos by using a colon: "Moscow helicopter views:1", or "Beethoven:1-9,12,14" to add first 9, 12th and 14th video for "Beethoven" query.&lt;br&gt;' +
                 'You can also enter one or multiple WN or youtube URLs, with or without http://, i.e. http://youtu.be/i8c5JcnFaJ0 or wn.com/parrot_drone_fun/latest/3,1,2,4-10/&lt;br&gt;' +
                 '&lt;textarea style="width:99%; height: 80%"&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;input type="button" onclick="do_import(this);" value="Create your Wn Instant Playlist!"&gt;' +
                 '&lt;img class="ifr_close" title="Click here to cancel" src="http://cdn4.wn.com/or/ula/ewn/closebox.png" onclick="login_close()" /&gt;',
        css: {
                width: '880px',
                height: '495px',
                top: '15%',
                applyPlatformOpacityRules: false,
                left: (parseInt((w - 880) * 50 / w) + '%'),
                border: '5px solid #eff2f3',
                backgroundColor: '#aaa',
                '-webkit-border-radius': '14px',
                '-moz-border-radius':    '14px',
                '-khtml-border-radius': '14px',
                'border-radius': '14px'
             }
    });
    return false;
});
   </script>

       <style>
        .wiki-page .reflist { display: none; }
       </style>
       <script type="text/javascript">

       <div class="wikiparser" data-custom="0" data-main="1" data-title="Night sky">
        <div class="mwcss wikisnippet">
         <div class="mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr ns-0 skin-vector">
          <div class="mwp">
           <img height="103" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Moonfromoakland04052006.jpg/120px-Moonfromoakland04052006.jpg" style="float:right; padding: 0 0 10px 10px" width="120"/>
           <p>
            The term
            <i>
             <b>
              night sky
             </b>
            </i>
            refers to the
            <a href="http://wn.com/Sky" title="Sky">
             sky
            </a>
            as seen at
            <a href="http://wn.com/Night" title="Night">
             night
            </a>
            . The term is usually associated with
            <a href="http://wn.com/Astronomy" title="Astronomy">
             astronomy
            </a>
            , with reference to views of
            <a href="http://wn.com/Celestial_bodies" title="Celestial bodies">
             celestial bodies
            </a>
            such as
            <a href="http://wn.com/Star" title="Star">
             stars
            </a>
            , the
            <a href="http://wn.com/Moon" title="Moon">
             Moon
            </a>
            , and
            <a href="http://wn.com/Planet" title="Planet">
             planets
            </a>
            that become visible on a clear night after the
            <a href="http://wn.com/Sun" title="Sun">
             Sun
            </a>
            has set. Natural light sources in a night sky include
            <a href="http://wn.com/Moonlight" title="Moonlight">
             moonlight
            </a>
            ,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Starlight" title="Starlight">
             starlight
            </a>
            , and
            <a href="http://wn.com/Airglow" title="Airglow">
             airglow
            </a>
            , depending on location and timing.
           </p>
           <p>
            The night sky and studies of it have a historical place in both ancient and modern
            <a class="mw-redirect" href="http://wn.com/Cultures" title="Cultures">
             cultures
            </a>
            . In the past, for instance,
            <a class="mw-redirect" href="http://wn.com/Farmers" title="Farmers">
             farmers
            </a>
            have used the state of the night sky as a
            <a href="http://wn.com/Calendar" title="Calendar">
             calendar
            </a>
            to determine when to plant
            <a href="http://wn.com/Agriculture" title="Agriculture">
             crops
            </a>
            . Many cultures have drawn
            <a href="http://wn.com/Constellation" title="Constellation">
             constellations
            </a>
            between
            <a href="http://wn.com/Star" title="Star">
             stars
            </a>
            in the sky, using them in association with
            <a href="http://wn.com/Legend" title="Legend">
             legends
            </a>
            and
            <a href="http://wn.com/Mythology" title="Mythology">
             mythology
            </a>
            about their
            <a class="mw-redirect" href="http://wn.com/Deities" title="Deities">
             deities
            </a>
            .
           </p>
           <p>
            The
            <a href="http://wn.com/History_of_astrology" title="History of astrology">
             anciently developed
            </a>
            belief of
            <a href="http://wn.com/Astrology" title="Astrology">
             astrology
            </a>
            is generally based on the belief that relationships between heavenly bodies influence or convey information about events on
            <a href="http://wn.com/Earth" title="Earth">
             Earth
            </a>
            . The
            <i>
             scientific
            </i>
            study of the night sky and bodies observed within it, meanwhile, takes place in the science of astronomy.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="wikipage">
         <a href="#" id="wiki_1" onclick="return load_wiki(this)" style="color: #55A4F2 !important">
          Read more...
         </a>
        </div>
        <br/>
        <br/>
        <br/>
        <div class="font_color">
         This page contains text from
         <a href="http://wikipedia.org/">
          Wikipedia, the Free Encyclopedia
         </a>
         -
         <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Night_sky">
          http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Night_sky
         </a>
         <br/>
         <br/>
         This article is licensed under the
         <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/">
          Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported License
         </a>
         ,
        which means that you can copy and modify it as long as the entire work (including additions) remains under this license.
        </div>
       </div>
       <br clear="left"/>
       <br clear="right"/>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="wiki-page" id="wiki1" style="display:none">
      <div class="center-content">
       <div class="wikiparser" data-custom="0" data-main="0" data-title="Night">
        <div class="mwcss wikisnippet">
         <div class="mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr ns-0 skin-vector">
          <div class="mwp">
           <img height="90" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3f/Rainbow_colored_Rainbow_Bridge_at_night.jpg/120px-Rainbow_colored_Rainbow_Bridge_at_night.jpg" style="float:right; padding: 0 0 10px 10px" width="120"/>
           <p>
            <b>
             Night
            </b>
            or
            <b>
             nighttime
            </b>
            is the period of
            <a href="http://wn.com/Time" title="Time">
             time
            </a>
            between the sunset and the sunrise when the
            <a href="http://wn.com/Sun" title="Sun">
             Sun
            </a>
            is below the
            <a href="http://wn.com/Horizon" title="Horizon">
             horizon
            </a>
            . This occurs after
            <a href="http://wn.com/Dusk" title="Dusk">
             dusk
            </a>
            . The opposite of night is
            <a href="http://wn.com/Day" title="Day">
             day
            </a>
            (or "
            <a href="http://wn.com/Daylight" title="Daylight">
             daytime
            </a>
            " to distinguish it from "day" as used for a 24-hour period). The start and end points of time of a night vary based on factors such as
            <a href="http://wn.com/Season" title="Season">
             season
            </a>
            ,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Latitude" title="Latitude">
             latitude
            </a>
            ,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Longitude" title="Longitude">
             longitude
            </a>
            and
            <a class="mw-redirect" href="http://wn.com/Timezone" title="Timezone">
             timezone
            </a>
            .
           </p>
           <p>
            At any given time, one side of the planet
            <a href="http://wn.com/Earth" title="Earth">
             Earth
            </a>
            is bathed in light from the Sun (the daytime) and the other side of the Earth is in the shadow caused by the Earth blocking the light of the sun. This shadow is what we call the darkness of night. Natural illumination is still provided by a combination of
            <a href="http://wn.com/Moonlight" title="Moonlight">
             moonlight
            </a>
            ,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Planet" title="Planet">
             planetary
            </a>
            light,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Starlight" title="Starlight">
             starlight
            </a>
            , diffuse
            <a href="http://wn.com/Zodiacal_light" title="Zodiacal light">
             zodiacal light
            </a>
            ,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Gegenschein" title="Gegenschein">
             gegenschein
            </a>
            , and
            <a href="http://wn.com/Airglow" title="Airglow">
             airglow
            </a>
            . In some circumstances,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Bioluminescence" title="Bioluminescence">
             bioluminescence
            </a>
            ,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Aurora_(astronomy)" title="Aurora (astronomy)">
             aurorae
            </a>
            and
            <a href="http://wn.com/Lightning" title="Lightning">
             lightning
            </a>
            can provide some illumination. The glow provided by artificial illumination is sometimes referred to as
            <a href="http://wn.com/Light_pollution" title="Light pollution">
             light pollution
            </a>
            because it can interfere with
            <a href="http://wn.com/Observational_astronomy" title="Observational astronomy">
             observational astronomy
            </a>
            and
            <a href="http://wn.com/Ecosystem" title="Ecosystem">
             ecosystems
            </a>
            .
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="wikipage">
         <a href="#" id="wiki_0" onclick="return load_wiki(this)" style="color: #55A4F2 !important">
          Read more...
         </a>
        </div>
        <br/>
        <br/>
        <br/>
        <div class="font_color">
         This page contains text from
         <a href="http://wikipedia.org/">
          Wikipedia, the Free Encyclopedia
         </a>
         -
         <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Night">
          http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Night
         </a>
         <br/>
         <br/>
         This article is licensed under the
         <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/">
          Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported License
         </a>
         ,
        which means that you can copy and modify it as long as the entire work (including additions) remains under this license.
        </div>
       </div>
       <br clear="left"/>
       <br clear="right"/>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="wiki-page" id="wiki2" style="display:none">
      <div class="center-content">
       <div class="wikiparser" data-custom="0" data-main="0" data-title="Sky">
        <div class="mwcss wikisnippet">
         <div class="mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr ns-0 skin-vector">
          <div class="mwp">
           <img height="90" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Sky_over_Washington_Monument.JPG/120px-Sky_over_Washington_Monument.JPG" style="float:right; padding: 0 0 10px 10px" width="120"/>
           <p>
            The
            <b>
             sky
            </b>
            , also known as the
            <b>
             celestial dome
            </b>
            , commonly refers to everything that lies a certain distance above the surface of
            <a href="http://wn.com/Earth" title="Earth">
             Earth
            </a>
            , including the
            <a href="http://wn.com/Atmosphere_of_Earth" title="Atmosphere of Earth">
             atmosphere
            </a>
            and the rest of
            <a href="http://wn.com/Outer_space" title="Outer space">
             outer space
            </a>
            . In the field of
            <a href="http://wn.com/Astronomy" title="Astronomy">
             astronomy
            </a>
            , the sky is also called the
            <b>
             <a href="http://wn.com/Celestial_sphere" title="Celestial sphere">
              celestial sphere
             </a>
            </b>
            . This is an imaginary dome where the sun, stars, planets, and the moon are seen to be traveling. The celestial sphere is divided into regions called
            <a href="http://wn.com/Constellation" title="Constellation">
             constellations
            </a>
            . Usually, the term sky is used from the point of view of the Earth's surface. However, the exact meaning of the term can vary; in some cases, the sky is defined as only the denser portions of the atmosphere, for example.
           </p>
           <p>
            During
            <a href="http://wn.com/Daylight" title="Daylight">
             daylight
            </a>
            , the sky appears to be
            <a href="http://wn.com/Blue" title="Blue">
             blue
            </a>
            because
            <a class="mw-redirect" href="http://wn.com/Air" title="Air">
             air
            </a>
            scatters blue
            <a href="http://wn.com/Sunlight" title="Sunlight">
             sunlight
            </a>
            more than it scatters red. At night, the sky appears to be a mostly dark surface or region scattered with
            <a href="http://wn.com/Star" title="Star">
             stars
            </a>
            . During the day, the
            <a href="http://wn.com/Sun" title="Sun">
             Sun
            </a>
            can be seen in the sky, unless obscured by
            <a href="http://wn.com/Cloud" title="Cloud">
             clouds
            </a>
            . In the
            <a href="http://wn.com/Night_sky" title="Night sky">
             night sky
            </a>
            (and to some extent during the day) the
            <a href="http://wn.com/Moon" title="Moon">
             moon
            </a>
            ,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Planet" title="Planet">
             planets
            </a>
            and stars are visible in the sky. Some of the natural phenomena seen in the sky are
            <a href="http://wn.com/Cloud" title="Cloud">
             clouds
            </a>
            ,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Rainbow" title="Rainbow">
             rainbows
            </a>
            , and
            <a class="mw-redirect" href="http://wn.com/Polar_Aurora" title="Polar Aurora">
             aurorae
            </a>
            .
            <a href="http://wn.com/Lightning" title="Lightning">
             Lightning
            </a>
            and
            <a href="http://wn.com/Precipitation_(meteorology)" title="Precipitation (meteorology)">
             precipitation
            </a>
            can also be seen in the sky during
            <a href="http://wn.com/Storm" title="Storm">
             storms
            </a>
            .
            <a href="http://wn.com/Bird" title="Bird">
             Birds
            </a>
            ,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Insect" title="Insect">
             insects
            </a>
            ,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Aircraft" title="Aircraft">
             aircraft
            </a>
            , and
            <a class="mw-redirect" href="http://wn.com/Kite_flying" title="Kite flying">
             kites
            </a>
            are often considered to
            <a href="http://wn.com/Flight" title="Flight">
             fly
            </a>
            in the sky. As a result of human activities,
            <a href="http://wn.com/Smog" title="Smog">
             smog
            </a>
            during the day and
            <a href="http://wn.com/Light_pollution" title="Light pollution">
             light pollution
            </a>
            during the night are often seen above large
            <a href="http://wn.com/City" title="City">
             cities
            </a>
            .
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="wikipage">
         <a href="#" id="wiki_0" onclick="return load_wiki(this)" style="color: #55A4F2 !important">
          Read more...
         </a>
        </div>

           The night sky offers an ever-changing display of fascinating objects you can see, from stars and constellations to bright planets, often the moon, and sometimes special events like meteor showers. 
Observing the night sky can be done with no special equipment.
Most of the astronomical events on this video can be seen with unaided eye, although some may require a good pair of binoculars for best viewing.

Enjoy the night sky

He used a Nikon D810A and the AF-S NIKKOR 1424 mm f2.8G ED lens, at 14 mm, f2.8, exposure 30s  1000 images, ISO 3200. The Nikon D810A is Nikon's first FX-format DSLR  DSLR dedicated to long-exposure deep-sky astrophotography http://bit.ly/photosD810A

Based on the award-winning full-frame D810, the D810A records the brilliant red tones of H-alpha emission nebulae with a level of detail and sharpness, wide dynamic range and rich tonality almost unimaginable until now. Reveal the faintest celestial objects with exposures up to 15 minutes long

           <a class="icon play mobile-hide" data-reveal-id="video-content" onclick="ensure(load_iframe_url)('modal-player', 'http://www.youtube.com/embed/68zFcuG8U5c?autoplay=1'); return false;">
           </a>

         <p class="caption">
          Night Sky - Speed Painting
         </p>
         <div class="video-fulltitle" style="display: none;">
          Night Sky - Speed Painting
         </div>
         <span class="description-content">
          <div class="tooltip-content-body">
           <h3>
            Night Sky - Speed Painting
           </h3>
           This is a time-lapse video of my latest space painting, it's acrylic on canvas.
Paint time for this was around 20 minutes, at most 30 if you take into account my moving the camera around. :P

This was a really fun video to shoot, and edit especially being able to see myself painting. Let me know if there is any of my art you would like to see in one of these videos, as I'm hoping to do more!

This painting is available in my etsy shop! 

Etsy: MarsupialPudding.etsy.com
Facebook: facebook.com/AshleighRoseProductions
Tumblr: MonstersInMyBathtub.tumblr.co
Instagram + Twitter: @AshuhleighRose

Song: Awake by Tycho
          </div>
         </span>
        </li>
       </ul>
      </div>

     <div id="music_data" style="display: none;">
      <div class="center-content">
       <script type="text/javascript">
        &lt;!--

            function do_query_add_to_playlist(query) {
                // search youtube for first match
                jQuery.ajax({
                    data: {
                        t: 'cheetah-photo-search/mvs_videosearch.txt',
                        query: query,

                    },
                    dataType: 'jsonp',
                    url: 'http://upge.wn.com/',
                    success: function(text) {
                        video_to_add = $(text).find('.video-info').first();
                        if (video_to_add.length &gt; 0) {
                            videoplayers[1].addVideo(video_to_add);
                        }
                        else {
                            var text = i18n("Could not find a suitable video for \"%s\" query");
                            $('#noresults').html(text.replace('%s', query));
                        }
                    }
                });
            }

             function do_query_add_to_fs_playlist(query) {
                // search youtube for first match
                jQuery.ajax({
                    data: {
                        t: 'cheetah-photo-search/mvs_videosearch.txt',
                        query: query,
                    },
                    dataType: 'jsonp',
                    url: 'http://upge.wn.com/',
                    success: function(text) {
                        video_to_add = $(text).find('.video-info').first();
                        if (video_to_add.length &gt; 0) {
                            videoplayer_fs.addVideo(video_to_add);
                        }
                        else {
                            var text = i18n("Could not find a suitable video for \"%s\" query");
                            $('#noresults').html(text.replace('%s', query));
                        }
                    }
                });
            }


            $ensure(function() {

                $('.instaplay-audioplayer').live('click', function(e) {
                    e.preventDefault();
                });
                $('#retrieve-playlist').live('click', function(e) {
                        $('.disco-check:checked').each(function(idx) {
                                query = $(this).next('a').attr('title');
                                do_query_add_to_playlist(query);
                        });
                });

                $('.disco-check').live('click', function(e) {
                        checks_on = $('.disco-check:checked').length;
                        if (checks_on &lt;= 1) {
                            $('#retrieve-playlist').html(i18n("Use checked songs to create your playlist"));
                        }
                        else {
                            var text = i18n("Use %s checked songs to add to your playlist");
                            $('#retrieve-playlist').html(text.replace('%s', '&lt;span class="num"&gt;' + checks_on + '&lt;/span&gt;'));
                        }
                });

                jQuery('.add-all-playlist').live('click', function(e) {
                    e.preventDefault();
                    jQuery(this).next('.disco-album-checkall').attr('checked', true);
                    jQuery('#retrieve-playlist').click();
                });


                jQuery('.add-playlist').live('click', function(e) {
                    e.preventDefault();
                    query = $(this).attr('id');
                    do_query_add_to_playlist(query);
                });


                jQuery('a.disco-album-checkall').live('click', function(e) {
                    e.preventDefault();
                    // deselect all other links on the page
                    jQuery('input.disco-check').attr('disabled', false);
                    jQuery('input.disco-check').attr('checked', false);
                    var links = $(this).parents('div.rel-head:first').next('ul.links');
                    links.find(':checkbox').each(function() {
                        $(this).click();
                    });
                });

                $('.toggle-tracks').live('click', function(e) {
                    tracks_list = $(this).parents('div.rel-head').next('ul.links');
                    if (tracks_list.length == 1) {
                        tracks_list.find('input.disco-check').click();
                    }
                });

                $('#retrieve-playlist').live('click', function(e) {
                    $('.disco-check:checked').each(function(idx) {
                        query = $(this).next('a').attr('title');
                        $(this).attr('checked', false);
                        $(this).attr('disabled', true);
                        do_query_add_to_playlist(query);
                    });
                });
                $('.retrieve-playlist').live('click', function(e) {
                        $('.disco-check:checked').each(function(idx) {
                                query = $(this).next('a').attr('title');
                                do_query_add_to_playlist(query);
                        });
                });
                $('.retrieve-fs-playlist').live('click', function(e) {
                        $('.disco-check:checked').each(function(idx) {
                                query = $(this).next('a').attr('title');
                                do_query_add_to_fs_playlist(query);
                        });
                });
                $('.retrieve-karaoke-playlist').live('click', function(e) {
                        $('.disco-check:checked').each(function(idx) {
                                query = $(this).next('a').attr('title');
                                do_query_add_to_fs_playlist(query + 'karaoke');
                        });
                });


            });
        // --&gt;
       </script>
      </div>
     </div>

             TOP Night Sky Events June 2015
            </h3>
            The night sky offers an ever-changing display of fascinating objects you can see, from stars and constellations to bright planets, often the moon, and sometimes special events like meteor showers. 
Observing the night sky can be done with no special equipment.
Most of the astronomical events on this video can be seen with unaided eye, although some may require a good pair of binoculars for best viewing.

Enjoy the night sky

He used a Nikon D810A and the AF-S NIKKOR 1424 mm f2.8G ED lens, at 14 mm, f2.8, exposure 30s  1000 images, ISO 3200. The Nikon D810A is Nikon's first FX-format DSLR  DSLR dedicated to long-exposure deep-sky astrophotography http://bit.ly/photosD810A

Based on the award-winning full-frame D810, the D810A records the brilliant red tones of H-alpha emission nebulae with a level of detail and sharpness, wide dynamic range and rich tonality almost unimaginable until now. Reveal the faintest celestial objects with exposures up to 15 minutes long

          <span class="description-content">
           <div class="tooltip-content-body">
            <h3>
             Night Sky - Speed Painting
            </h3>
            This is a time-lapse video of my latest space painting, it's acrylic on canvas.
Paint time for this was around 20 minutes, at most 30 if you take into account my moving the camera around. :P

This was a really fun video to shoot, and edit especially being able to see myself painting. Let me know if there is any of my art you would like to see in one of these videos, as I'm hoping to do more!

This painting is available in my etsy shop! 

Etsy: MarsupialPudding.etsy.com

         <div class="video-fulldescription font_color">
          The night sky offers an ever-changing display of fascinating objects you can see, from stars and constellations to bright planets, often the moon, and sometimes special events like meteor showers. 
Observing the night sky can be done with no special equipment.
Most of the astronomical events on this video can be seen with unaided eye, although some may require a good pair of binoculars for best viewing.

Enjoy the night sky

SEA &amp; SKY
http://www.seasky.org/astronomy/astronomy-calendar-2015.html

SPACE.COM
http://www.space.com/16149-night-sky.html

EARTH SKY
http://earthsky.org/

2 Pallas
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2_Pallas

Music credit: YouTube Audio Library
Intro - Hero Theme (sting) - MK2
2)  Lonesome Avenue -  The 126ers
3) Satin Sugar - Huma-Huma

        <span class="description-content" style="display: none;">
         <div class="tooltip-content-body">
          The night sky offers an ever-changing display of fascinating objects you can see, from stars and constellations to bright planets, often the moon, and sometimes special events like meteor showers. 
Observing the night sky can be done with no special equipment.
Most of the astronomical events on this video can be seen with unaided eye, although some may require a good pair of binoculars for best viewing.

Enjoy the night sky

SEA &amp; SKY
http://www.seasky.org/astronomy/astronomy-calendar-2015.html

SPACE.COM
http://www.space.com/16149-night-sky.html

EARTH SKY
http://earthsky.org/

2 Pallas
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2_Pallas

Music credit: YouTube Audio Library

2)  Lonesome Avenue -  The 126ers

         <div class="video-fulldescription font_color">
          Something to listen while stargazing the night sky in the northern hemisphere untill spring arrives.

01. Brian Eno - Prophecy Theme
02. Jonn Serrie - Deep Mystery (4:35)
03. Rudy Adrian - Under Orion (10:21)
04. Stellardrone - Billions And Billions (14:20)
05. Solar Empire - Beneath The Stars (18:55)
06. Jonn Serrie - The traits Of Madigann (28:36)
07. Clint Mansell - The Last Man (35:22)
08. Bruno Sanfilippo - Piano Textures III (40:18)
09. Kevin Kendle - Winter Jasmine (44:40)
10. Vangelis - Come To Me (46:58)
11. David Helpling &amp; Jon Jenkins - The Same Sky (50:44)
12. Susumu Yokota - Saku (55:46)
13. Rudy Adrian - Promise of Snow (1:00:44)
14. Ian Boddy - The Possibility of Existence (1:04:36)
15. Vangelis - Ask the Mountains (1:06:30)
16. Ulrich Schnauss - Einfeld (1:12:06)
17. Sysyphe - Sinking (1:15:37)
18. Carbon Based Lifeforms - Init (1:23:29)
19. Michael Stearns - As The Earth Kissed the Moon (1:30:02)
20. Moby - God Moving Over ohe Face of the Waters (1:33:40)
21. Art of Noise - Moments in Love (1:40:37)
         </div>

          http://wn.com/Epicuros_-_The_Winter_Night_Sky_(Ambient,_Chillout,_Atmospheric)
         </a>

         <div class="tooltip-content-body">
          Something to listen while stargazing the night sky in the northern hemisphere untill spring arrives.

2015 Grand Canyon Star Party: http://go.nps.gov/gcstarparty

Grand Canyon In Depth is a video podcast series that explores the natural and human history of Grand Canyon National Park. Produced by the National Park Service in association with Bristlecone Media and Grand Canyon Association, the official nonprofit partner of Grand Canyon National Park.

        <div class="content font_color">
         <div class="video-thumb border_color bgr_color playvideo1" onclick="return triggerFullscreen(1);">
          <img alt="Jewels of the night sky: time-lapse video, Chile - Nikon D810A" height="225" src="http://i.ytimg.com/vi/7iqqokBxYIY/0.jpg" style="display: block;" title="Jewels of the night sky: time-lapse video, Chile - Nikon D810A" width="300"/>
         </div>
         <input class="details-manual-order" size="2" type="text" value=""/>
         <div class="video-title font_color">
          Jewels of the night sky: time-lapse video, Chile - Nikon D810A
         </div>
         <ul class="font_color">
          <li>
           <span data-trans="Order:">
            Order:
           </span>
           <input class="details-manual-order" size="2" type="text" value="12"/>
           <a class="details-manual-order-confirm" href="javascript:void(0);" style="display:none;" title="Move to new position">
            Reorder
           </a>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span data-trans="Duration:">
            Duration:
           </span>
           <span class="video-duration">
            0:35
           </span>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span data-trans="Updated:">
            Updated:
           </span>
           <span class="video-uploaded">
            07 Jul 2015
           </span>
          </li>
         </ul>
         <br/>
         <div class="video-fulldescription font_color">
          Sit back and enjoy this time-lapse video shot by Johannes Schedler at the CTIO observatory in Chile. He used a Nikon D810A and the AF-S NIKKOR 1424 mm f2.8G ED lens, at 14 mm, f2.8, exposure 30s  1000 images, ISO 3200. The Nikon D810A is Nikon's first FX-format DSLR  DSLR dedicated to long-exposure deep-sky astrophotography http://bit.ly/photosD810A

Based on the award-winning full-frame D810, the D810A records the brilliant red tones of H-alpha emission nebulae with a level of detail and sharpness, wide dynamic range and rich tonality almost unimaginable until now. Reveal the faintest celestial objects with exposures up to 15 minutes long; and noise-free performance at ISO levels as high as 12,800 (expandable to 51,000). Create star trail images that span the entire sky with unlimited continuous JPEG shooting. Whether using a fixed tripod, equatorial mount, connected to a telescope or tethered to a laptop, the D810A can take your passion for the cosmos out of this world.
         </div>
         <a class="video-wnlink" href="http://wn.com/Jewels_of_the_night_sky_time-lapse_video,_Chile_-_Nikon_D810A" style="target-name: new; target-new: tab;" target="_blank">
          http://wn.com/Jewels_of_the_night_sky_time-lapse_video,_Chile_-_Nikon_D810A
         </a>

         <div class="video-fulldescription font_color">
          This is a time-lapse video of my latest space painting, it's acrylic on canvas.
Paint time for this was around 20 minutes, at most 30 if you take into account my moving the camera around. :P

This was a really fun video to shoot, and edit especially being able to see myself painting. Let me know if there is any of my art you would like to see in one of these videos, as I'm hoping to do more!

This painting is available in my etsy shop! 

Etsy: MarsupialPudding.etsy.com
Facebook: facebook.com/AshleighRoseProductions
Tumblr: MonstersInMyBathtub.tumblr.co
Instagram + Twitter: @AshuhleighRose

How Gravity Shapes the Universe

The universe is filled with spectacular objects, from gloriously-coloured nebulae to the swirling motion of a billion stars formed into a single galaxy. One force has created it all - gravity. The Sky at Night team steps away from the bright lights and travels to the Brecon Beacons AstroCamp to see how gravity shapes the universe in all its glory. Maggie Aderin-Pocock asks why so much of the night sky is filled with spheres and why not all these

          <span class="description-content">
           <div class="tooltip-content-body">
            <h3>
             Documentary on Stars HD
            </h3>
            A star is a massive, luminous sphere of plasma held together by its own gravity. The nearest star to Earth is the Sun, which is the source of most of the planet's energy. Other stars are visible from Earth during the night, appearing as a multitude of fixed luminous points due to their immense distance. Historically, the most prominent stars were grouped into constellations and asterisms, and the brightest stars gained proper names. Extensive catalogues of stars have been assembled by astronomers, which provide standardized star designations.

For at least a portion of its life, a star shines due to thermonuclear fusion of hydrogen into heliu

          <img alt="BBC The Sky at Night - How Gravity Shapes the Universe [HD]" height="225" src="http://i.ytimg.com/vi/ij4qf10iar4/0.jpg" style="display: block;" title="BBC The Sky at Night - How Gravity Shapes the Universe [HD]" width="300"/>

         <div class="video-fulldescription font_color">
          Science Documentary hosted by Chris Lintott and Maggie Aderin-Pocock, published by BBC broadcasted as part of BBC The Sky at Night series in 2014 - English narration


How Gravity Shapes the Universe

The universe is filled with spectacular objects, from gloriously-coloured nebulae to the swirling motion of a billion stars formed into a single galaxy. One force has created it all - gravity. The Sky at Night team steps away from the bright lights and travels to the Brecon Beacons AstroCamp to see how gravity shapes the universe in all its glory. Maggie Aderin-Pocock asks why so much of the night sky is filled with spheres and why not all these spheres are what they seem. Chris Lintott finds out about the newest moon in the solar system that has just formed in Saturn's rings, and how it could shed light on how the planets formed billions of years ago. Plus, how to get great images of the night sky without using a telescope and what the shape of a galaxy tells you about its past.

Thanks to: MVGroup; JungleBoy;
         </div>
         <a class="video-wnlink" href="http://wn.com/BBC_The_Sky_at_Night_-_How_Gravity_Shapes_the_Universe_HD_" style="target-name: new; target-new: tab;" target="_blank">
          http://wn.com/BBC_The_Sky_at_Night_-_How_Gravity_Shapes_the_Universe_HD_
         </a>

         <div class="tooltip-content-body">

         <br/>
         <div class="video-fulldescription font_color">
          Happy New Years!
This was on sale so I decided to download it.

This is a very interesting and original game.
I'm not a big fan of puzzle games but this is quite fun.
Basically, you control the direction of the ball and must travel to the end.
Its also very relaxing. I could listen to the soundtrack all day (too bad some of it is copyrighted).
Anyway, I go through the first 2 areas: Harara Mountains and Skymining.
As you can see in the beginning I messed up on the cropping. Hopefully it doesn't show up too badly.

       <div class="video-desc border_color {source: 'youtube', video_id: 'QCYS1LJtKyM', duration: 3637, published: '27 Oct 2014', updated: '27 Oct 2014', video_views: '0'}">
        <div class="content font_color">
         <div class="video-thumb border_color bgr_color playvideo2" onclick="return triggerFullscreen(2);">
          <img alt="Documentary on Stars HD" height="225" src="http://i.ytimg.com/vi/QCYS1LJtKyM/0.jpg" style="display: block;" title="Documentary on Stars HD" width="300"/>
         </div>
         <input class="details-manual-order" size="2" type="text" value=""/>
         <div class="video-title font_color">
          Documentary on Stars HD
         </div>
         <ul class="font_color">
          <li>
           <span data-trans="Order:">
            Order:
           </span>
           <input class="details-manual-order" size="2" type="text" value="18"/>
           <a class="details-manual-order-confirm" href="javascript:void(0);" style="display:none;" title="Move to new position">
            Reorder
           </a>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span data-trans="Duration:">
            Duration:
           </span>
           <span class="video-duration">
            60:37
           </span>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span data-trans="Updated:">
            Updated:
           </span>
           <span class="video-uploaded">
            27 Oct 2014
           </span>
          </li>
         </ul>
         <br/>
         <div class="video-fulldescription font_color">
          A star is a massive, luminous sphere of plasma held together by its own gravity. The nearest star to Earth is the Sun, which is the source of most of the planet's energy. Other stars are visible from Earth during the night, appearing as a multitude of fixed luminous points due to their immense distance. Historically, the most prominent stars were grouped into constellations and asterisms, and the brightest stars gained proper names. Extensive catalogues of stars have been assembled by astronomers, which provide standardized star designations.

For at least a portion of its life, a star shines due to thermonuclear fusion of hydrogen into helium in its core, releasing energy that traverses the star's interior and then radiates into outer space. Once the hydrogen in the core of a star is nearly exhausted, almost all naturally occurring elements heavier than helium are created by stellar nucleosynthesis during the star's lifetime and, for some stars, by supernova nucleosynthesis when it explodes. Near the end of its life, a star can also contain degenerate matter. Astronomers can determine the mass, age, metallicity (chemical composition), and many other properties of a star by observing its motion through space, luminosity, and spectrum respectively. The total mass of a star is the principal determinant of its evolution and eventual fate. Other characteristics of a star, including diameter and temperature, change over its life, while the star's environment affects its rotation and movement. A plot of the temperature of many stars against their luminosities, known as a HertzsprungRussell diagram (HR diagram), allows the age and evolutionary state of a star to be determined.

A star's life begins with the gravitational collapse of a gaseous nebula of material composed primarily of hydrogen, along with helium and trace amounts of heavier elements. Once the stellar core is sufficiently dense, hydrogen becomes steadily converted into helium through nuclear fusion, releasing energy in the process. The remainder of the star's interior carries energy away from the core through a combination of radiative and convective processes. The star's internal pressure prevents it from collapsing further under its own gravity. Once the hydrogen fuel at the core is exhausted, a star with at least 0.4 times the mass of the Sun expands to become a red giant, in some cases fusing heavier elements at the core or in shells around the core. The star then evolves into a degenerate form, recycling a portion of its matter into the interstellar environment, where it will contribute to the formation of a new generation of stars with a higher proportion of heavy elements. Meanwhile, the core becomes a stellar remnant: a white dwarf, a neutron star, or (if it is sufficiently massive) a black hole.

Binary and multi-star systems consist of two or more stars that are gravitationally bound, and generally move around each other in stable orbits. When two such stars have a relatively close orbit, their gravitational interaction can have a significant impact on their evolution. Stars can form part of a much larger gravitationally bound structure, such as a star cluster or a galaxy.
         </div>
         <a class="video-wnlink" href="http://wn.com/Documentary_on_Stars_HD" style="target-name: new; target-new: tab;" target="_blank">
          http://wn.com/Documentary_on_Stars_HD
         </a>
         <br clear="left"/>
         <div class="detailsBar border_color bgr_color">
          <a class="play" data-reveal-id="video-content" onclick="ensure(load_iframe_url)('modal-player', 'http://www.youtube.com/embed/QCYS1LJtKyM?autoplay=1'); return false;">
           <span data-trans="Play">
            Play
           </span>
          </a>
          <a class="fs playvideo2" href="javascript: void(0);" onclick="return triggerFullscreen(2);">
           <span data-trans="Fullscreen">
            Fullscreen
           </span>
          </a>
          <!-- &lt;a class="videoremove" href="javascript: void(0);"&gt;&lt;span data-trans="Remove from playlist"&gt;Remove from playlist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; -->
         </div>
        </div>
        <span class="description-content" style="display: none;">
         <div class="tooltip-content-body">
          A star is a massive, luminous sphere of plasma held together by its own gravity. The nearest star to Earth is the Sun, which is the source of most of the planet's energy. Other stars are visible from Earth during the night, appearing as a multitude of fixed luminous points due to their immense distance. Historically, the most prominent stars were grouped into constellations and asterisms, and the brightest stars gained proper names. Extensive catalogues of stars have been assembled by astronomers, which provide standardized star designations.

For at least a portion of its life, a star shines due to thermonuclear fusion of hydrogen into helium in its core, releasing energy that traverses the star's interior and then radiates into outer space. Once the hydrogen in the core of a star is nearly exhausted, almost all naturally occurring elements heavier than helium are created by stellar nucleosynthesis during the star's lifetime and, for some stars, by supernova nucleosynthesis when it explodes. Near the end of its life, a star can also contain degenerate matter. Astronomers can determine the mass, age, metallicity (chemical composition), and many other properties of a star by observing its motion through space, luminosity, and spectrum respectively.
