Other characteristics of a star, including diameter and temperature, change over its life, while the star's environment affects its rotation and movement. A plot of the temperature of many stars against their luminosities, known as a HertzsprungRussell diagram (HR diagram), allows the age and evolutionary state of a star to be determined.

A star's life begins with the gravitational collapse of a gaseous nebula of material composed primarily of hydrogen, along with helium and trace amounts of heavier elements. Once the stellar core is sufficiently dense, hydrogen becomes steadily converted into helium through nuclear fusion, releasing energy in the process. The remainder of the star's interior carries energy away from the core through a combination of radiative and convective processes. The star's internal pressure prevents it from collapsing further under its own gravity. Once the hydrogen fuel at the core is exhausted, a star with at least 0.4 times the mass of the Sun expands to become a red giant, in some cases fusing heavier elements at the core or in shells around the core. The star then evolves into a degenerate form, recycling a portion of its matter into the interstellar environment, where it will contribute to the formation of a new generation of stars with a higher proportion of heavy elements. Meanwhile, the core becomes a stellar remnant: a white dwarf, a neutron star, or (if it is sufficiently massive) a black hole.

Binary and multi-star systems consist of two or more stars that are gravitationally bound, and generally move around each other in stable orbits. When two such stars have a relatively close orbit, their gravitational interaction can have a significant impact on their evolution. Stars can form part of a much larger gravitationally bound structure, such as a star cluster or a galaxy.

"Friday Night Lights Original Soundtrack" (2004)

Produced and Recorded in Burbank, California by Brian Reitzell, Justin Stanley and Richard Jory June and August 2004

00:00 From West Texas 
02:37 Your Hand In Mine (w/strings) 
06:42 Our Last Days As Children 
09:19 An Ugly Fact of Life 
12:11 Home 
- omitted - Sonho Dourado - Daniel Lanois - 
14:45 To West Texas 
18:46 Your Hand In Mine (Goodbye) 
20:43 Inside It All Feels The Same 
- omitted  - Do You Ever Feel Cursed - David Torn -
25:03 Lonely Train 
- omitted - Seagull - Bad Company - 
31:51 The Sky Above, The Field Below 
37:17 A Slow Dance 

Every once in awhile someone asks us how we ended up working on a big studio movie about football. The simplest answer is that we got an email. This particular email was from Brian Reitzell who was the music supervisor for both The Virgin Suicides and Lost In Translation (two movies that we are quite fond of). He said he was working on a new movie and he was wondering if we would be interested in doing music for it. We told him we would. He got back in touch with us a few days later and told us that the movie he was working on was called Friday Night Lights. He didn't really have to explain much as we were somewhat familiar with the book and even more familiar with the setting of the story. West Texas. Midland and Odessa. This is the part of Texas where three out of the four of us grew up. We all read the book and we loved it. It was sad and joyful and depressing and triumphant and funny and ugly and exciting. We said yes. Several months later we found ourselves in a studio in Burbank, staring at a movie screen and trying to write music. Our fears of having weird movie producers and studio executives hovering over us were completely unfounded. It was just us, Brian Reitzell and two friendly Australian engineers (Justin Stanley and Richard Jory). We were surrounded by all sorts of rare equipment (vintage drum machines, rare keyboards and organs, strange percussion devices). We didn't really use any of it. We just stuck with what we knew. There was also a kitchen that was stocked with great quantities of snacks. Chips, cookies, several boxes of Twizzlers, etc. It was delightful. We were in the middle of a tour and in New York City the day in October that the movie opened. We hurried through our soundcheck and literally ran to the closest theater. We got our tickets and sat down and watched the movie. Then we left and ran back to the venue and played our show.


Amazon Editorial Reviews, Product Description
Novelist H. G. Bissinger's story about a high school football team in Texas went to the big screen with Billy Bob Thornton in the lead role. The score and background music was largely composed for the film by indie faves Explosions in the Sky, with a little help from Daniel Lanois, David Torn, and Bad Company. Producer Brian Reitzell has gone against convention in designing musical atmospheres for the film that don't conform either to the martial music generally associated with football or the C&amp;W associated with Texas. Instead, he opted for a more autumnal, introspective sound that serves as a perfect backdrop for the film, but also stands up on its own without benefit of any other audio-visual cues. 

AMG Review by James Christopher Monger
For small-town America, high-school football is a religion. The home team in Peter Berg's Friday Night Lights has to travel over 250 miles of sun-parched southwest highway to meet their rival team, and who better to paint those Texas skies than the Lone Star State's own Explosions in the Sky? Soundtrack producer Brian Reitzell, whose fluid work on The Virgin Suicides and Lost in Translation is instantly recognizable here, throws Daniel Lanois, David Torn, and Bad Company into the mix as well, resulting in a collection of music that redirects its intended genre into something altogether spiritual. Sports dramas usually rely on an infuriating blend of swelling strings and "We Will Rock You" bombast, so it's a real treat to hear the post rock quartet's guitar-driven soundscapes illuminating camera close-ups of down-to-the-wire scoreboards and off-field bonding. The wistful, string-driven "Your Hand in Mine" -- courtesy of arranger and father of Beck, David Campbell -- is as close to "traditional" as Friday Night Lights gets, but the atmospheric centerpiece owes a lot more to Brian Eno than it does John Williams. Much of the material was culled from bits and pieces of the band's two Temporary Residence releases -- the director had grown used to them in the context of the work print of the film -- then combined with all-new compositions, making FNL a must-have for fans, but it's the patient way the soundtrack unfolds, Bad Company and all, that gives it an edge over soulless, hit-driven opponents like Remember the Titans or Any Given Sunday.
         </div>

         </a>

37:17 A Slow Dance 

Every once in awhile someone asks us how we ended up working on a big studio movie about football. The simplest answer is that we got an email. This particular email was from Brian Reitzell who was the music supervisor for both The Virgin Suicides and Lost In Translation (two movies that we are quite fond of). He said he was working on a new movie and he was wondering if we would be interested in doing music for it. We told him we would. He got back in touch with us a few days later and told us that the movie he was working on was called Friday Night Lights. He didn't really have to explain much as we were somewhat familiar with the book and even more familiar with the setting of the story. West Texas. Midland and Odessa. This is the part of Texas where three out of the four of us grew up. We all read the book and we loved it. It was sad and joyful and depressing and triumphant and funny and ugly and exciting. We said yes. Several months later we found ourselves in a studio in Burbank, staring at a movie screen and trying to write music. Our fears of having weird movie producers and studio executives hovering over us were completely unfounded. It was just us, Brian Reitzell and two friendly Australian engineers (Justin Stanley and Richard Jory). We were surrounded by all sorts of rare equipment (vintage drum machines, rare keyboards and organs, strange percussion devices). We didn't really use any of it. We just stuck with what we knew. There was also a kitchen that was stocked with great quantities of snacks. Chips, cookies, several boxes of Twizzlers, etc. It was delightful. We were in the middle of a tour and in New York City the day in October that the movie opened. We hurried through our soundcheck and literally ran to the closest theater. We got our tickets and sat down and watched the movie. Then we left and ran back to the venue and played our show.


Amazon Editorial Reviews, Product Description
Novelist H. G. Bissinger's story about a high school football team in Texas went to the big screen with Billy Bob Thornton in the lead role. The score and background music was largely composed for the film by indie faves Explosions in the Sky, with a little help from Daniel Lanois, David Torn, and Bad Company. Producer Brian Reitzell has gone against convention in designing musical atmospheres for the film that don't conform either to the martial music generally associated with football or the C&amp;W associated with Texas. Instead, he opted for a more autumnal, introspective sound that serves as a perfect backdrop for the film, but also stands up on its own without benefit of any other audio-visual cues. 

AMG Review by James Christopher Monger
For small-town America, high-school football is a religion. The home team in Peter Berg's Friday Night Lights has to travel over 250 miles of sun-parched southwest highway to meet their rival team, and who better to paint those Texas skies than the Lone Star State's own Explosions in the Sky? Soundtrack producer Brian Reitzell, whose fluid work on The Virgin Suicides and Lost in Translation is instantly recognizable here, throws Daniel Lanois, David Torn, and Bad Company into the mix as well, resulting in a collection of music that redirects its intended genre into something altogether spiritual. Sports dramas usually rely on an infuriating blend of swelling strings and "We Will Rock You" bombast, so it's a real treat to hear the post rock quartet's guitar-driven soundscapes illuminating camera close-ups of down-to-the-wire scoreboards and off-field bonding. The wistful, string-driven "Your Hand in Mine" -- courtesy of arranger and father of Beck, David Campbell -- is as close to "traditional" as Friday Night Lights gets, but the atmospheric centerpiece owes a lot more to Brian Eno than it does John Williams. Much of the material was culled from bits and pieces of the band's two Temporary Residence releases -- the director had grown used to them in the context of the work print of the film -- then combined with all-new compositions, making FNL a must-have for fans, but it's the patient way the soundtrack unfolds, Bad Company and all, that gives it an edge over soulless, hit-driven opponents like Remember the Titans or Any Given Sunday.

            ESOcast 65: The Chilean Sky in Ultra High Definition

In the Spring of 2014, a team of ESO Photo ambassadors embarked on a pioneering expedition to ESO's three observatories in Chile. Their mission was to capture a wide range of images and time-lapses of the magnificent Chilean night sky and landscape in crisp Ultra High Definition. Join our heroes in their adventures in the arid Atacama Desert as they bring our Universe closer than ever before.

More episodes of the ESOcast are also available.

Feature
* 
Mit der Deckenleuchte NIGHT SKY zaubern Sie einen romantischen Sternenhimmel in Ihr Zuhause. Die Spots sind schwenkbar und mit dem integrierten Serienschalter individuell schaltbar. 1 Stufe - Nur die LEDs gehen an, 2 Stufe - Nur die Spots gehen an, 3 Stufe - Alle Spots und LEDs gehen an LED-Kette 12 x 10.Optional erhltlich als:- Paul Neuhaus, Deckenleuchte Night Sky 3-flammig- Paul Neuhaus, Deckenleuchte Night Sky 6-flammigWohnstil:Typ: TrendLeuchte, Lampe:Typ: DeckenlampeAusstattung Leuchte, Lampe:Leistung je Leuchtmittel: 20 WattSpannung: 12 VoltMaterial Leuchte, Lampe:Gehuse: MetallFassung:Typ: GU5,3Mae Leuchte, Lampe:Durchmesser: 75 cm (ca.)
http://www.amazon.de/dp/B0056YMPBM?tag=management0b-21
         </div>
         <a class="video-wnlink" href="http://wn.com/Paul_Neuhaus_Deckenleuchte_Night_Sky_5_Spots_und_120" style="target-name: new; target-new: tab;" target="_blank">
          http://wn.com/Paul_Neuhaus_Deckenleuchte_Night_Sky_5_Spots_und_120
         </a>

Feature
* 
Mit der Deckenleuchte NIGHT SKY zaubern Sie einen romantischen Sternenhimmel in Ihr Zuhause. Die Spots sind schwenkbar und mit dem integrierten Serienschalter individuell schaltbar. 1 Stufe - Nur die LEDs gehen an, 2 Stufe - Nur die Spots gehen an, 3 Stufe - Alle Spots und LEDs gehen an LED-Kette 12 x 10.Optional erhltlich als:- Paul Neuhaus, Deckenleuchte Night Sky 3-flammig- Paul Neuhaus, Deckenleuchte Night Sky 6-flammigWohnstil:Typ: TrendLeuchte, Lampe:Typ: DeckenlampeAusstattung Leuchte, Lampe:Leistung je Leuchtmittel: 20 WattSpannung: 12 VoltMaterial Leuchte, Lampe:Gehuse: MetallFassung:Typ: GU5,3Mae Leuchte, Lampe:Durchmesser: 75 cm (ca.)

         <div class="video-fulldescription font_color">
          ESOcast 65: The Chilean Sky in Ultra High Definition

In the Spring of 2014, a team of ESO Photo ambassadors embarked on a pioneering expedition to ESO's three observatories in Chile. Their mission was to capture a wide range of images and time-lapses of the magnificent Chilean night sky and landscape in crisp Ultra High Definition. Join our heroes in their adventures in the arid Atacama Desert as they bring our Universe closer than ever before.

More episodes of the ESOcast are also available.

Find out how to view and contribute subtitles for the ESOcast in multiple languages, or translate this video on dotSUB.

Credit:http://www.eso.org/public/videos/esocast65a/

ESO

Visual design and editing: Martin Kornmesser and Luis Cal?ada.
Editing: Herbert Zodet.
Web and technical support: Mathias Andr and Raquel Yumi Shida.
Written by: Ryan Laird and Herbert Zodet.
Narration: Sara Mendes da Costa.
Music: Johan B. Monell (www.johanmonell.com).
Footage and photos: ESO, Y. Beletsky (LCO), Christoph Malin (christophmalin.com), Babak Tafreshi (twanight.org) and Luis Cal?ada.
Directed by: Herbert Zodet.
Executive producer: Lars Lindberg Christensen.

         <div class="video-thumb border_color bgr_color playvideo3" onclick="return triggerFullscreen(3);">
          <img alt="Paragliding - morocco sky charme" height="225" src="http://i.ytimg.com/vi/b-jPOxEWw6I/0.jpg" style="display: block;" title="Paragliding - morocco sky charme" width="300"/>

         <br/>
         <div class="video-fulldescription font_color">
          www.greattravel-morocco.com
Join us on one of our inspirational guided paragliding safaris in Morocco. Get away from Europe for the most reliable paragliding conditions this spring and autumn - from the sweetest thermals, to sand-dune flying and deserted coastal ridge soaring. Paraglide Morocco!
No electricity, no running water...
no bars, no discos, dusty roads, and sometimes the simplest of accommodation. We travel by 4x4 vehicle to find the best flying and give you an extravagant cultural experience visiting remote parts of Morocco inhabited by the mythical Berber tribes. The scenery is breath-taking, enchanting and very exotic. Fly in the setting sun with the magical Atlas mountains and Saharan desert as backdrops. Swoop through the African skies as the scenery changes through incredible shades of crimson and scarlet, shades of saffron yellow, lilac and purple. See the brightest star-filled night skies. Enjoy delicious Moroccan cuisine from aromatic and spicy tagines to succulent fruit and of course the ubiquitous mint tea.
Safaris
The safari-style nature of our trips means we have the freedom to explore Moroccos paragliding potential to the maximum, (and drink up some amazing scenery along the way). All PASSION safaris are one week long and have a maximum of 10-12 people. Our most popular safari is the classic High Atlas Safari: now in its 12th successful season. From Marrakech we head directly into the High Atlas mountains. You can expect to be flying from day one at Aguergour our main base for this trip and probably the most famous site in Morocco. Our excursions include ascents of some of the highest mountains in North Africa with donkeys packing those heavy wings and harnesses for us. We also visit Test on the southern side of the High Atlas mountains to fly high above the Sous valley and distant Saharan desert.
         </div>
         <a class="video-wnlink" href="http://wn.com/Paragliding_-_morocco_sky_charme" style="target-name: new; target-new: tab;" target="_blank">
          http://wn.com/Paragliding_-_morocco_sky_charme
         </a>

        <span class="description-content" style="display: none;">
         <div class="tooltip-content-body">
          www.greattravel-morocco.com
Join us on one of our inspirational guided paragliding safaris in Morocco. Get away from Europe for the most reliable paragliding conditions this spring and autumn - from the sweetest thermals, to sand-dune flying and deserted coastal ridge soaring. Paraglide Morocco!
No electricity, no running water...
no bars, no discos, dusty roads, and sometimes the simplest of accommodation. We travel by 4x4 vehicle to find the best flying and give you an extravagant cultural experience visiting remote parts of Morocco inhabited by the mythical Berber tribes. The scenery is breath-taking, enchanting and very exotic. Fly in the setting sun with the magical Atlas mountains and Saharan desert as backdrops. Swoop through the African skies as the scenery changes through incredible shades of crimson and scarlet, shades of saffron yellow, lilac and purple. See the brightest star-filled night skies. Enjoy delicious Moroccan cuisine from aromatic and spicy tagines to succulent fruit and of course the ubiquitous mint tea.
Safaris
The safari-style nature of our trips means we have the freedom to explore Moroccos paragliding potential to the maximum, (and drink up some amazing scenery along the way). All PASSION safaris are one week long and have a maximum of 10-12 people. Our most popular safari is the classic High Atlas Safari: now in its 12th successful season. From Marrakech we head directly into the High Atlas mountains. You can expect to be flying from day one at Aguergour our main base for this trip and probably the most famous site in Morocco. Our excursions include ascents of some of the highest mountains in North Africa with donkeys packing those heavy wings and harnesses for us. We also visit Test on the southern side of the High Atlas mountains to fly high above the Sous valley and distant Saharan desert.

     <script>
      function update_chat_position(el){
    if(!el.length) return;
    var name = $(el).data('tab');
    var content = $(el).closest('.playlistformating').find('.tab-content.'+name);
    var co = content.offset();
    var po = {left: 0, top: 0}; //content.closest('.playlist-page').offset();
    var ao = $('#chat-box').parent().offset();
    var left = co.left - po.left - ao.left;
    var top = co.top - po.top - ao.top;
    if (name == 'tab-2') {
        $('#chat-box').attr('style','').css({display:'block', position:'absolute', left: left, top: top, 'z-index': 100});

        var chatIframe = document.getElementById('chat-iframe');
        if (!chatIframe.src) {
            chatIframe.onload = function() {
                var targetOrigin;
                targetOrigin = 'http://chat.wn.com';
                var targetUrl;
                if (document.URL.indexOf('#') &gt; 0) {
                    targetUrl = document.URL;
                } else {
                    targetUrl = document.URL + '#/videos/chat';
                }
                chatIframe.contentWindow.postMessage({parentUrl:targetUrl},
                                                     chatIframe.dataset.src);
                console.log('URL msg sent to iframe');
            }
            chatIframe.src = chatIframe.dataset.src;
        }
    } else {
        $('#chat-box').hide();
    }
}
$('.tab-link').live('click', function(){update_chat_position($(this))});
     </script>

      <style>
       #chat-box {
    height: 569px;
    min-width: 320px;
    width: 348px;
    transition: top .4s ease-out, left .4s ease-out, width .4s ease-out, height .4s ease-out;
}

      <script>
       function receiveMessageFromIFrame(event) {
    //console.log('new message received:');
    //console.log(event.data);
    try {
        var chatBox = $('#chat-box');
        if (event.data.fullscreen) {
            chatBox.data('position', chatBox.css('position'));
            chatBox.data('display', chatBox.css('display'));
            chatBox.data('top', chatBox.css('top'));
            chatBox.data('left', chatBox.css('left'));
            chatBox.data('z-index', chatBox.css('z-index'));
            document.getElementById('header_login').scrollIntoView();
            chatBox.css({
                position: 'fixed',
                top: 22,
                bottom: 130,
                left: 0,
                right: 0,
                height: ($(window).height() - 22) + 'px',
                width: '100%',
                zIndex: 99999,
            });
            $('#playlist1').css('display', 'none');
            $('body').css('overflow', 'hidden');
            $('#header').css('display', 'none');
        } else if (event.data.fullscreen != undefined) {
            //$('#playlist1').css('z-index', '');
            $('#playlist1').css('display', 'block');
            $('body').css('overflow', '');
            $('#header').css('display', '');
            chatBox.css({
                'position': chatBox.data('position'),
                'display': chatBox.data('display'),
                'top': chatBox.data('top'),
                'left': chatBox.data('left'),
                //'z-index': chatBox.data('z-index'),
                'width': '',
                'height': '',
                'bottom': '',
                'right': ''
            });
            setTimeout(function() {
                chatBox.css({
                    'z-index': chatBox.data('z-index'),
                    });
            }, 300);
            //$('#chat-box').css({
            //    position: '',
            //    top: '',
            //    left: '',
            //    bottom: '',
            //    right: '',
            //    height: '',
            //    width: '',
            //    zIndex: '',
            //});
        }
    } catch (err) {
        console.log(err);
    }
}
window.addEventListener("message", receiveMessageFromIFrame, false);

    //data-src="http://localhost:9080"
    //data-src="http://test.chat.wn.com"
      </script>

                $ensure(function(){
                        $('a#play0').click(function(){
                            videoplayers[0].addVideo($('#details0 .video-info'));
                            videoplayers[0].addVideo($('#playlist0 .video-info'));
                        });
                        $('a#remove0').click(function(){
                            $('#playlist0 .mainvideoresults').animate({ opacity: 'hide' }, "slow");
                            updateHeight();
                        });
                        $('a.list-preview').click(function(){
                            $('.list-preview').hide('fast');
                            $('.thumb-preview').show('fast');
                        });
                        $('a.thumb-preview').click(function(){
                            $('.list-preview').show('fast');
                            $('.thumb-preview').hide('fast');
                        });
                        $('#playlist_clear0').click(function(){
                            $(this).hide('fast');
                            $('#playlist_restore0').show('fast');
                         });
                        $('#playlist_restore0').click(function(){
                            $('.playlist_clear0').show('fast');
                            $(this).hide('fast');
                        });
                        $('#sortby0').hide();
                        $('a#open_sortby0').click(function(){
                            $('#sortby0').show('slow');
                            $('#open_sortby0').hide('fast');
                            $('#close_sortby0').show('fast');
                        });
                        $('a#close_sortby0').click(function(){
                            $('#sortby0').hide('slow');
                            $('#open_sortby0').show('fast');
                            $('#close_sortby0').hide('fast');
                        });
                        jQuery(document).keyup(function(e) {
                        if (e.keyCode == 27) {
                            jQuery('#home0').click();
                            return false;
                            }
                        });
                });

              <div class="tooltip-content-body">
               <h3>
                TOP Night Sky Events June 2015
               </h3>
               The night sky offers an ever-changing display of fascinating objects you can see, from stars and constellations to bright planets, often the moon, and sometimes special events like meteor showers. 
Observing the night sky can be done with no special equipment.
Most of the astronomical events on this video can be seen with unaided eye, although some may require a good pair of binoculars for best viewing.

Enjoy the night sky

SEA &amp; SKY
http://www.seasky.org/astronomy/astronomy-calendar-2015.html

SPACE.COM
http://www.space.com/16149-night-sky.html

EARTH SKY
http://earthsky.org/

2 Pallas
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2_Pallas

Intro - Hero Theme (sting) - MK2
2)  Lonesome Avenue -  The 126ers
3) Satin Sugar - Huma-Huma

11. David Helpling &amp; Jon Jenkins - The Same Sky (50:44)
12. Susumu Yokota - Saku (55:46)
13. Rudy Adrian - Promise of Snow (1:00:44)
14. Ian Boddy - The Possibility of Existence (1:04:36)
15. Vangelis - Ask the Mountains (1:06:30)
16. Ulrich Schnauss - Einfeld (1:12:06)
17. Sysyphe - Sinking (1:15:37)
18. Carbon Based Lifeforms - Init (1:23:29)
19. Michael Stearns - As The Earth Kissed the Moon (1:30:02)
20. Moby - God Moving Over ohe Face of the Waters (1:33:40)
21. Art of Noise - Moments in Love (1:40:37)

                Night Sky - Grand Canyon In Depth Episode 04
               </h3>
               http://go.nps.gov/gcnightsky  Journey to a place where the Milky Way stretches across the heavens. Experience the mystery and wonder of Grand Canyon's night sky with Astronomer Tyler Nordgren and Park Ranger Rader Lane. Explore its beauty and learn what you can do to help preserve it. 

2015 Grand Canyon Star Party: http://go.nps.gov/gcstarparty

Grand Canyon In Depth is a video podcast series that explores the natural and human history of Grand Canyon National Park. Produced by the National Park Service in association with Bristlecone Media and Grand Canyon Association, the official nonprofit partner of Grand Canyon National Park.

             <div class="video-fulltitle" style="display: none;">
              Jewels of the night sky: time-lapse video, Chile - Nikon D810A
             </div>
             <span class="description-content" style="display: none;">
              <div class="tooltip-content-body">
               <h3>
                Jewels of the night sky: time-lapse video, Chile - Nikon D810A
               </h3>
               Sit back and enjoy this time-lapse video shot by Johannes Schedler at the CTIO observatory in Chile. He used a Nikon D810A and the AF-S NIKKOR 1424 mm f2.8G ED lens, at 14 mm, f2.8, exposure 30s  1000 images, ISO 3200. The Nikon D810A is Nikon's first FX-format DSLR  DSLR dedicated to long-exposure deep-sky astrophotography http://bit.ly/photosD810A

Based on the award-winning full-frame D810, the D810A records the brilliant red tones of H-alpha emission nebulae with a level of detail and sharpness, wide dynamic range and rich tonality almost unimaginable until now. Reveal the faintest celestial objects with exposures up to 15 minutes long; and noise-free performance at ISO levels as high as 12,800 (expandable to 51,000). Create star trail images that span the entire sky with unlimited continuous JPEG shooting. Whether using a fixed tripod, equatorial mount, connected to a telescope or tethered to a laptop, the D810A can take your passion for the cosmos out of this world.

              <div class="tooltip-content-body">
               <h3>
                Night Sky - Speed Painting
               </h3>
               This is a time-lapse video of my latest space painting, it's acrylic on canvas.
Paint time for this was around 20 minutes, at most 30 if you take into account my moving the camera around. :P

This was a really fun video to shoot, and edit especially being able to see myself painting. Let me know if there is any of my art you would like to see in one of these videos, as I'm hoping to do more!

This painting is available in my etsy shop! 

Etsy: MarsupialPudding.etsy.com
Facebook: facebook.com/AshleighRoseProductions
Tumblr: MonstersInMyBathtub.tumblr.co
Instagram + Twitter: @AshuhleighRose

Song: Awake by Tycho

                        $('a#play1').click(function(){
                            videoplayers[1].addVideo($('#details1 .video-info'));
                            videoplayers[1].addVideo($('#playlist1 .video-info'));
                        });
                        $('a#remove1').click(function(){
                            $('#playlist1 .mainvideoresults').animate({ opacity: 'hide' }, "slow");
                            updateHeight();
                        });
                        $('a.list-preview').click(function(){
                            $('.list-preview').hide('fast');
                            $('.thumb-preview').show('fast');
                        });
                        $('a.thumb-preview').click(function(){
                            $('.list-preview').show('fast');
                            $('.thumb-preview').hide('fast');
                        });
                        $('#playlist_clear1').click(function(){
                            $(this).hide('fast');
                            $('#playlist_restore1').show('fast');
                         });
                        $('#playlist_restore1').click(function(){
                            $('.playlist_clear1').show('fast');
                            $(this).hide('fast');
                        });
                        $('#sortby1').hide();
                        $('a#open_sortby1').click(function(){
                            $('#sortby1').show('slow');
                            $('#open_sortby1').hide('fast');
                            $('#close_sortby1').show('fast');
                        });
                        $('a#close_sortby1').click(function(){
                            $('#sortby1').hide('slow');
                            $('#open_sortby1').show('fast');
                            $('#close_sortby1').hide('fast');
                        });
                        jQuery(document).keyup(function(e) {
                        if (e.keyCode == 27) {
                            jQuery('#home1').click();
                            return false;
                            }
                        });
                });
                // --&gt;
      </script>

             </div>
             <span class="description-content" style="display: none;">
              <div class="tooltip-content-body">
               <h3>
                BBC The Sky at Night - How Gravity Shapes the Universe [HD]
               </h3>
               Science Documentary hosted by Chris Lintott and Maggie Aderin-Pocock, published by BBC broadcasted as part of BBC The Sky at Night series in 2014 - English narration


How Gravity Shapes the Universe

The universe is filled with spectacular objects, from gloriously-coloured nebulae to the swirling motion of a billion stars formed into a single galaxy. One force has created it all - gravity. The Sky at Night team steps away from the bright lights and travels to the Brecon Beacons AstroCamp to see how gravity shapes the universe in all its glory. Maggie Aderin-Pocock asks why so much of the night sky is filled with spheres and why not all these spheres are what they seem. Chris Lintott finds out about the newest moon in the solar system that has just formed in Saturn's rings, and how it could shed light on how the planets formed billions of years ago. Plus, how to get great images of the night sky without using a telescope and what the shape of a galaxy tells you about its past.

Thanks to: MVGroup; JungleBoy;

             <span class="description-content" style="display: none;">
              <div class="tooltip-content-body">
               <h3>
                NightSky (3DS) Playthrough-Part 1
               </h3>
               Happy New Years!
This was on sale so I decided to download it.

This is a very interesting and original game.
I'm not a big fan of puzzle games but this is quite fun.
Basically, you control the direction of the ball and must travel to the end.
Its also very relaxing. I could listen to the soundtrack all day (too bad some of it is copyrighted).
Anyway, I go through the first 2 areas: Harara Mountains and Skymining.
As you can see in the beginning I messed up on the cropping. Hopefully it doesn't show up too badly.

                ESOcast 65: The Chilean Sky in Ultra High Definition | By  Amazing Space Documentary |
               </h3>
               ESOcast 65: The Chilean Sky in Ultra High Definition

In the Spring of 2014, a team of ESO Photo ambassadors embarked on a pioneering expedition to ESO's three observatories in Chile. Their mission was to capture a wide range of images and time-lapses of the magnificent Chilean night sky and landscape in crisp Ultra High Definition. Join our heroes in their adventures in the arid Atacama Desert as they bring our Universe closer than ever before.

More episodes of the ESOcast are also available.

Find out how to view and contribute subtitles for the ESOcast in multiple languages, or translate this video on dotSUB.

Credit:http://www.eso.org/public/videos/esocast65a/

ESO

Visual design and editing: Martin Kornmesser and Luis Cal?ada.
Editing: Herbert Zodet.
Web and technical support: Mathias Andr and Raquel Yumi Shida.
Written by: Ryan Laird and Herbert Zodet.
Narration: Sara Mendes da Costa.
Music: Johan B. Monell (www.johanmonell.com).
Footage and photos: ESO, Y. Beletsky (LCO), Christoph Malin (christophmalin.com), Babak Tafreshi (twanight.org) and Luis Cal?ada.
Directed by: Herbert Zodet.
Executive producer: Lars Lindberg Christensen.

                        });

                        });
                        $('a.list-preview').click(function(){
                            $('.list-preview').hide('fast');
                            $('.thumb-preview').show('fast');
                        });
                        $('a.thumb-preview').click(function(){
                            $('.list-preview').show('fast');
                            $('.thumb-preview').hide('fast');
                        });
                        $('#playlist_clear3').click(function(){
                            $(this).hide('fast');
                            $('#playlist_restore3').show('fast');
                         });
                        $('#playlist_restore3').click(function(){
                            $('.playlist_clear3').show('fast');
                            $(this).hide('fast');
                        });
                        $('#sortby3').hide();
                        $('a#open_sortby3').click(function(){
                            $('#sortby3').show('slow');
                            $('#open_sortby3').hide('fast');

                        });

                            $('#close_sortby3').hide('fast');
                        });

                        if (e.keyCode == 27) {
                            jQuery('#home3').click();
                            return false;
                            }
                        });
                });

      <script type="text/javascript">
       &lt;!--
        function findOrAddPlaylist(query, title, callback){
            var foundPlaylist = null;
            $('#playlist_menu li a').each(function(i){
                if($(this).text() == title) {
                    foundPlaylist = + $(this).attr('id').replace('#playlist','');
                }
            });

            if(foundPlaylist != null){
                callback('loading', foundPlaylist);
                callback('loaded', foundPlaylist);
            } else {
                _add_dynamic_playlist(query, title, callback, 0, true);
            }
        }

        function playQuery(vsid, query, title){
                var playlist = findOrAddPlaylist(query, title, function(status, num){
                    if(status == 'loading'){
                        $(".interview-play").hide();
                        $(".interview-play-off").show();
                    }
                    if(status == 'loaded'){
                        $(".interview-play").hide();
                        $(".interview-play-off").show();
                        // $('div#playlist'+num).find('li.playlistitemli:first').find('a.playlistitem:first').click();
                        videoplayers[num].playVideo();
                    }
                    if(status == 'failed'){
                        $(".interview-play-off").hide();
                        $("#wiki"+vsid+" .interview-play-none").show();
                        $("#wiki"+vsid+" .interview-play").remove();
                        $("#wiki"+vsid+" .interview-play-off").remove();
                    }
                });
        }

        jQuery(function() {
             jQuery('.interview-play-off').click(function() {
                $(".interview-play-off").hide();
                $(".interview-play").show();
                $(".videoplayer-control-pause").click();
            });

        });

    jQuery(".upper-block .show_author_videos").live("click", function() {
                   query = $(this).attr('title');
                   jQuery.ajax({
                            url: '/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/videoresults',
                            data: {'query': query},
                            success: function(text) {
                                        if(!text) { text = i18n("No results"); }
                                        jQuery('.video-desc-results').html(jQuery(text));
                                        jQuery('.description_box').css('height', $('.description_box').height() + 220);
                                        updateHeight();
                                    }
                    });
    });

    jQuery(".video-desc .show_author_videos").live("click", function() {
                        query = $(this).attr('title');
                        container   = $(this).parent().parent().parent().find('.video-author-thumbs');
                        $(this).parent().parent().parent().find('.video-author-thumbs').css('height', '220px');
                    jQuery.ajax({
                            url: '/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/videoresults',
                            data: {'query': query},
                            success: function(text) {
                                        if(!text) { text = i18n("No results"); }
                                        container.html(jQuery(text));
                                    }
                       });
    });

      <script type="text/javascript">
       &lt;!--
    // store search history to be able to control offset
    var currentSearchesPages = new Object;
    var currentMultiSearchesPages = {youtube: {},
                     vimeo: {},
                     dailymotion: {},
                     yahoo: {},
                     blip: {}
                    }

    window.currentMultiSearchesPages = currentMultiSearchesPages;

    jQuery(".more_related_mvs").live("click", function() {
        var parent = jQuery(this).parent().parent();
        var data = parent.metadata();
        if (currentMultiSearchesPages[data.source][data.query] == undefined) {
            currentMultiSearchesPages[data.source][data.query] = 0;
        }
        jQuery.ajax({
            data: {
                t: 'cheetah-photo-search/mvs_videosearch03.txt',
                orderby: 'published',
                corpus: 'current',
                language_id: '1',
                query: data.query,
                video_sources: data.source,
                page: currentMultiSearchesPages[data.source][data.query] + 1
            },
            dataType: 'jsonp',
            url: 'http://upge.wn.com/',
            success: function(text) {
            currentMultiSearchesPages[data.source][data.query] += 1;
            parent.append(jQuery(text));
        }
        });
    });




    function find_multiple_video() {
                   window.activateTab('playlist1');
                   jQuery('#multiple_video').show('fast');
                   var query = jQuery("#videoquery0").val();
                   offset = last_count;
                   last_count += 8;

                var query_spaceless = query.replace(' ', '');
                if ($('#main_div_'+query_spaceless).length &gt; 0) return;

                   var fquery = query.replace(/[\W\s]+/i, '_');

                   if (currentSearchesPages[fquery] == undefined) {
                       currentSearchesPages[fquery] = 0;
                   }
                   window.currentSearchesPages = currentSearchesPages;

                   jQuery.ajax({
                           data: {
                           t: 'cheetah-photo-search/mvs_videosearch03.txt',
                           orderby: 'published',
                           corpus: 'current',
                           language_id: '1',
                           query: query,
                           offset: offset,
                           page: currentSearchesPages[fquery]
                    },
                    dataType: 'jsonp',
                    url: 'http://upge.wn.com/',
                    success: function(text) {
                            jQuery('#multiple_video').prepend(jQuery(text));
                            window.currentSearchesPages[fquery] += 1;
                            updateHeight();
                    },
                    complete: function() {
                        //theForm.find('input[type=submit]').attr('disabled', '');
                        //$('html,body').animate({ scrollTop: $('#multiple_video').offset().top }, { duration: 'slow', easing: 'swing'});
                    }
                });
    }
   function load_lyrics(query, artist) {
        jQuery.ajax({
            url: '/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/lyrics',
            data: {'query': query,
                   'artist': artist
            },
            success: function(text) {
            if(!text) { text = i18n("No lyrics available"); }
                jQuery('#lyrics_text').html(text);
                updateHeight();
            }
        });
        return false;
    }

    function load_publications(source_id) {
        var id = source_id
        jQuery.ajax({
               url: '/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/source_results',
               data: {'source_id': source_id},
                success: function(text) {
                if(!text) { text = i18n("No results"); }
                jQuery('#timeline_results').html(text);
                jQuery('#news_stories').hide();
                 jQuery('#timeline_results').show();
                jQuery('.timeline a').removeClass('bold');
                updateHeight();

            }
           });
     }



    function load_language_results(query, lang){
        jQuery.ajax({
            url: '/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/lang_results',
            data: { 'query': query,
                    'language_id': lang
            },
            success: function(text) {
                if(!text) { text = i18n("No results"); }
                jQuery('#language .center-content').html(text);
                updateHeight('#language');
            }
        });
        return false;
     }

    function load_timeline_results(query, year){
        jQuery('#news_stories').hide();
        jQuery('#timeline_results').show().html('&lt;p style="padding: 80px 0;"&gt;loading...&lt;/p&gt;');
        jQuery.ajax({
            url: '/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/timeline',
            data: { 'query': query,
                    'year': year
            },
			dataType: 'jsonp',
            success: function(text) {
                if(!text) { text = i18n("No results"); }
                jQuery('#timeline_results').html(text);

                jQuery('.timeline a').removeClass('bold');
                updateHeight();

            }
        });
        return false;
     }
    jQuery('div.next_prev a').live('click', function(e) {
        e.preventDefault();
        jQuery('#timeline_results').html("Loading...");
        jQuery('#timeline_results').scrollTop(10);
        jQuery('#timeline_results').load(jQuery(this).attr('href'));

    });


    function load_related_videos() {
        jQuery.ajax({
            url: '/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/related_videos',
            data: {'query': 'night sky'},
            dataType: 'jsonp',
            success: function(text) {
            if(!text) { text = i18n("No related videos"); }
                jQuery('div#rel_videos').html(text);
            }
        });
    }





    function find_more_videos() {
                  var query = 'night sky';
                  offset = last_count;
                  last_count += 8;
                  jQuery.ajax({
                          data: {
                          t: 'cheetah-photo-search/mvs_showmore01.txt',
                          offset: offset,
                          orderby: 'published',
                          corpus: 'current',
                          language_id: '1',
                          query: query
                      },
                      dataType: 'jsonp',
                      url: 'http://upge.wn.com/',
                      success: function(text) {
                              jQuery('#searchresults').prepend(jQuery(text));
                      }
                  });
      }
      function more_videos() {
                  var query = 'night sky';
                  jQuery.ajax({
                          data: {
                          t: 'cheetah-photo-search/showmore.txt',
                          offset: '20',
                          query: query
                      },
                      dataType: 'jsonp',
                      url: 'http://upge.wn.com/',
                      success: function(text) {
                              jQuery('#more_video_results').prepend(jQuery(text));
                              jQuery('more_videos').hide();

                      }
                  });
      }

          var wn_search_mangler = function(theform) {
          find_multiple_video();
          return false;
        }

        // --&gt;

        function initMORE(){
            var theForm = jQuery('#more_242373130');
            theForm.submit(function(event) {
            event.preventDefault();
            var id = jQuery("#id_242373130").val();
            jQuery.ajax({
             url: '/api/upge/worldnews/more',
             data: { id: id },
                     success: function(text) {
                    jQuery('div#search-loading').addClass('show');
                    jQuery('div#search-loading').removeClass('hide');
                    jQuery('#more_box_242373130').append(jQuery(text));

                },
             complete: function() {
                    jQuery('div#search-loading').addClass('hide');
                    jQuery('div#search-loading').removeClass('show');
                    jQuery('.submit_242373130').addClass('hide');
                }
            });
            });

                    jQuery('div#search-loading').addClass('show');
                    jQuery('div#search-loading').removeClass('hide');
                    jQuery('#more_box_242360348').append(jQuery(text));

                },
             complete: function() {
                    jQuery('div#search-loading').addClass('hide');
                    jQuery('div#search-loading').removeClass('show');
                    jQuery('.submit_242360348').addClass('hide');
                }
            });
            });
            var theForm = jQuery('#more_242357308');

        jQuery('#news-search').click(function(event) {
                var ss = jQuery("#video_query").val().toLowerCase().replace(/[:\.\/_ ]+/g, '_');
                $.cookies.set('wnsearch', ss);
                window.location = 'http://wn.com/' + ss;
                return false; // do not submit the form
            });
        jQuery('#form-news-search').submit(function(event) {
                var ss = jQuery("#video_query").val().toLowerCase().replace(/[:\.\/_ ]+/g, '_');
                $.cookies.set('wnsearch', ss);
                window.location = 'http://wn.com/' + ss.replace(' ', '_');
                return false; // do not submit the form
            });
            //jQuery('#multiple-video-search').click(function(e) {
            //    find_multiple_video();
            //    event.preventDefault();
            //});
        });

        <script type="text/javascript">
         &lt;!--
        function triggerFullscreen(vsid){
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('position', 'fixed');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('top', '70px');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('left', '0');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('bottom', '0');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('z-index', '113');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('width', '100%');

        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('background-color', '#000000');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('div.active').css('position', 'fixed');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('div.active').css('width', '100%');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('div.active').css('top', '70px');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('div.active').css('bottom', '0px');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('div.active').css('left', '0');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('object').attr('width', '100%');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('object').attr('height', $(window).height() -70);
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('embed').attr('width', '100%');
        jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('embed').attr('height', $(window).height() - 70);
        jQuery('#home'+vsid).show();
        jQuery('.fs-class').hide();
        jQuery('.muteFS'+vsid).show();
        jQuery('.footer_links').hide();
        videoplayers[vsid].playVideo();
        jQuery('.videoplayer-control-play'+vsid).click();
        jQuery('body').css('overflow', 'hidden');
        return false;
        }
        function doneFullscreen(vsid){
                jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('position', 'relative');
        		jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('top', '0px');
                jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('width', '640px');
                jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('height', '390px');
                jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).css('z-index', '102');
                jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('div.active').css('position', 'absolute');
                jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('div.active').css('width', '640px');
                jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('div.active').css('height', '390px');
        		jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('div.active').css('top', '0px');
                jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('object').attr('width', '640px');
                jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('object').attr('height', '390px');
                jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('embed').attr('width', '640px');
                jQuery('#playercontainer'+vsid).find('embed').attr('height', '390px ');
                jQuery('#home'+vsid).hide();
              
        		jQuery('.fs-class').show();
                jQuery('.footer_links').show();
                jQuery('.muteFS'+vsid).hide();
                jQuery('body').css('overflow', 'auto');
                videoplayers[vsid].pauseVideo();

        return false;
        }
    jQuery(document).keyup(function(e) {
            if (e.keyCode == 27) {
        jQuery('.slimScrollDiv').css('position', 'relative');
                jQuery('.slimScrollDiv').css('width', '100%');
                jQuery('.slimScrollDiv').css('height', '360px');
        jQuery('#autoscroll').css('height', '360px');
                jQuery('.slimScrollDiv').css('z-index', '102');
        jQuery('.slimScrollDiv').css('position', 'relative');
        jQuery('#scrolling-play-pause').removeClass('fs');
        jQuery('.slimScrollDiv').removeClass('fs');
                return false;
            }
        });

    //--&gt;
        </script>

'&lt;span class="duration"&gt;&lt;%= durationStr %&gt;&lt;/span&gt;' +
'&lt;span class="description-content" style="display:none;"&gt;&lt;%= tooltipContentBody %&gt;&lt;/span&gt;' +

            playpositionTemplate: '&lt;%= elapsedTime %&gt; / &lt;%= totalTime %&gt;',

        videoplayers[1].playerContainer.bind('videoplayer.player.videoloaded', function(e, videoInfo){
            if(window.username &amp;&amp; videoInfo){
                $.ajax({url: 'http://login.wn.com/history/play/', data: {
                            video: videoInfo.source+':'+videoInfo.video_id,
                            title: videoInfo.title,
                            duration: videoInfo.duration
                        }, dataType:'jsonp'});
            }
            load_playlistlyrics(videoInfo.title);
        });

        jQuery('.autoplay').attr('checked', jQuery('#autoplay1').attr('checked'));
        jQuery('.autoplay').click(function(event){
            $('.autoplay').attr('checked', $(event.target).attr('checked'));
            videoplayers[1].onAutoplayClick();
        });
            var videoplayer = videoplayers[1];


        // this will add all available videos to playlist
        $ensure(function() {
                videoplayers[1].addVideo($('#video-results-1 .video-info').slice(0, 14));

            videoplayers[1].loadPlaylist();

            jQuery('#videoplayer-play-all1').click(function(event) {
                event.preventDefault();
                videoplayers[1].clearPlaylist();
                videoplayers[1].addVideo(jQuery('#video-results-1 .video-info').slice(0, 23));
                videoplayers[1].playPlaylist();
            });
            jQuery('#videoplayer-play-next1').click(function(event) {
                event.preventDefault();
                videoplayers[1].playNextPlaylistVideo();
            });
            jQuery('#playlist_restore1').click(function(event) {
                    event.preventDefault();
                    videoplayers[1].clearPlaylist();
                    videoplayers[1].addVideo(jQuery('#video-results-1 .video-info').slice(0, 14));
                    videoplayers[1].playPlaylist();
            });
            $('.play_all_fs_1').click(function(event){
                videoplayers[1].playPlaylist();
                triggerFullscreen(1);
            });
            $.fn.clickToggle = function(func1, func2) {
                var funcs = [func1, func2];
                this.data('toggleclicked', 0);
                this.click(function() {
                    var data = $(this).data();
                    var tc = data.toggleclicked;
                    $.proxy(funcs[tc], this)();
                    data.toggleclicked = (tc + 1) % 2;
                });
                return this;
            };

            $('.playlist_mute_1').clickToggle(function() {
                videoplayers[1].setVolumeMute();
                $(this).css('background-position', '0px 0px');
            }, function() {
                videoplayers[1].setVolumeUnMute();
                $(this).css('background-position', '-16px 0px');
            });
            $('.muteFS1').clickToggle(function() {
                videoplayers[1].setVolumeMute();
                $(this).css('background-position', '-30px center');
            }, function() {
                videoplayers[1].setVolumeUnMute();
                $(this).css('background-position', '0px center');
            });

            window.onPlayVideo1 = function(event) {
                videoplayers[1].log('onPlayVideo');
                event.preventDefault();
                var videoData = videoplayers[1].extractVideoData($(event.currentTarget));
                videoplayers[1].log(videoData);
                videoplayers[1].playFromPlaylist(videoData, this.AUTOSTART);
            };

            jQuery('.playvideo1').livequery(function() {
                $(this).click(window.onPlayVideo1);
            });
        });

            enableLogging: false,
            playTrigger: '.playvideo3',
            addTrigger: '.addvideo3',
            playlistRepeat: '#playlistrepeat3',
            playlistShuffle: '#playlistshuffle3',
            playlistClear: '.playlist_clear3',
            playposition: '#playposition3',
            autoplayCheckbox: '#autoplay3',
            replaycurrentCheckbox: '.replaycurrent3',
            autoplayCookie: '',
            playlistFormatCookie: 'wn-videoplayer-playlist-format',
            controlNext: '.videoplayer-control-next3',
            controlPrev: '.videoplayer-control-prev3',
            controlPlay: '.videoplayer-control-play3',
            controlPause: '.videoplayer-control-pause3',
            playlistLink: '.playlist-link'
        });
        videoplayers[3].playerContainer.bind('videoplayer.player.videoloaded', function(e, videoInfo){
            if(window.username &amp;&amp; videoInfo){
                $.ajax({url: 'http://login.wn.com/history/play/', data: {
                            video: videoInfo.source+':'+videoInfo.video_id,
                            title: videoInfo.title,
                            duration: videoInfo.duration
                        }, dataType:'jsonp'});
            }
            load_playlistlyrics(videoInfo.title);
        });

        jQuery('.autoplay').attr('checked', jQuery('#autoplay1').attr('checked'));
        jQuery('.autoplay').click(function(event){
            $('.autoplay').attr('checked', $(event.target).attr('checked'));
            videoplayers[1].onAutoplayClick();
        });


        // this will add all available videos to playlist
        $ensure(function() {
                videoplayers[3].addVideo($('#video-results-3 .video-info').slice(0, 14));

            videoplayers[3].loadPlaylist();

            jQuery('#videoplayer-play-all3').click(function(event) {
                event.preventDefault();
                videoplayers[3].clearPlaylist();
                videoplayers[3].addVideo(jQuery('#video-results-3 .video-info').slice(0, 23));
                videoplayers[3].playPlaylist();
            });
            jQuery('#videoplayer-play-next3').click(function(event) {
                event.preventDefault();
                videoplayers[3].playNextPlaylistVideo();
            });
            jQuery('#playlist_restore3').click(function(event) {
                    event.preventDefault();
                    videoplayers[3].clearPlaylist();
                    videoplayers[3].addVideo(jQuery('#video-results-3 .video-info').slice(0, 14));
                    videoplayers[3].playPlaylist();
            });
            $('.play_all_fs_3').click(function(event){
                videoplayers[3].playPlaylist();
                triggerFullscreen(3);
            });
            $.fn.clickToggle = function(func1, func2) {
                var funcs = [func1, func2];
                this.data('toggleclicked', 0);
                this.click(function() {
                    var data = $(this).data();
                    var tc = data.toggleclicked;
                    $.proxy(funcs[tc], this)();
                    data.toggleclicked = (tc + 1) % 2;
                });
                return this;
            };

            $('.playlist_mute_3').clickToggle(function() {
                videoplayers[3].setVolumeMute();
                $(this).css('background-position', '0px 0px');
            }, function() {
                videoplayers[3].setVolumeUnMute();
                $(this).css('background-position', '-16px 0px');
            });
            $('.muteFS3').clickToggle(function() {
                videoplayers[3].setVolumeMute();
                $(this).css('background-position', '-30px center');
            }, function() {
                videoplayers[3].setVolumeUnMute();
                $(this).css('background-position', '0px center');
            });

            window.onPlayVideo3 = function(event) {
                videoplayers[3].log('onPlayVideo');
                event.preventDefault();
                var videoData = videoplayers[3].extractVideoData($(event.currentTarget));
                videoplayers[3].log(videoData);
                videoplayers[3].playFromPlaylist(videoData, this.AUTOSTART);
            };

            jQuery('.playvideo3').livequery(function() {
                $(this).click(window.onPlayVideo3);
            });
        });

        // adding more actions
        $ensure(function() {
            jQuery('.submenu li a').click(function(event) {
                var id = $(event.target).attr('id');
                if(id.substring(0, 9) == '#playlist'){
                    window.videoplayer = videoplayers[parseInt(id.substring(9))];
                }
            });
            // hyphenate video details
            // only use this for english language
            jQuery('.video-info').each(function() {
                Hyphenator.hyphenate(this, 'en');
            });

            window.onAddVideo = function(event) {
                videoplayer.log('onAddVideo');
                event.preventDefault();
                var videoData = videoplayer.extractVideoData($(event.currentTarget));
                var playlist = videoplayer.getPlaylist();
                playlist.push(videoData);
                videoplayer.setPlaylist(playlist);
                videoplayer.log('onAddVideo done.');
            };

            jQuery('.addvideo').livequery(function() {
                $(this).click(window.onAddVideo);
            });
        });
    //--&gt;
        </script>
       </div>
       <!-- upper-block ends -->
       <script type="text/javascript">
        &lt;!--
        function ie_find_flash(){
            for(var i=8; i&gt;0; i--){
                flashVersion = 0;
                try{
                    var flash = new ActiveXObject("ShockwaveFlash.ShockwaveFlash." + i);
                    flashVersion = i;
                    return i;
                }
                catch(e){
                }
            }
            return 0;
        }
        function is_istuff() {
            var agent=navigator.userAgent.toLowerCase();
            var is_iPhone = (agent.indexOf('iphone')!=-1);
            var is_iPad = (agent.indexOf('ipad')!=-1);
            return (is_iPhone || is_iPad);
        }
        istuff = is_istuff();
        // hide the upper-block if Flash is not supported, for iPhone etc.
        var divname = 'upper-block';
        var element;
        var flash_supported = 0;
        if( document.getElementById ) // this is the way the standards work
            element = document.getElementById( divname );
        else if( document.all ) // this is the way old msie versions work
            element = document.all[divname];
        else if( document.layers ) // this is the way nn4 works
            element = document.layers[divname];

        // works on netscape and all sensible browsers
        if( navigator.mimeTypes["application/x-shockwave-flash"] ){
            flash_supported = 1;
        }else{
            flash_supported = ie_find_flash()
        }
        // iphone or ipad youtube videos can be embedded too

        if(!flash_supported &amp;&amp; !istuff){
            element.style.display = 'none';
        }
        //--&gt;
       </script>
      </div>

          <input class="query" id="news-query" name="query" onblur="if (this.value == '') {this.value = 'news search';}" onfocus="if (this.value == 'news search') {this.value = '';}" type="text" value="news search"/>

         <div class="close_rss font_color" style="font-weight: bold; margin: -15px 0 10px 0; cursor: pointer;">
           back to news headlines

        <script type="text/javascript">
         &lt;!--
        $ensure(function() {
           $('a.loadRss').click(ensure(function() {
                             $('.news_results').hide();
                             $('.news_stories').hide();
                             $('.rss_iframe').show();
                            if ($('#rssIframe').attr('src') == $(this).attr('href')) {
                                return false;
                            }
                            $('#rssIframe').attr('src', $(this).attr('href'));
                            updateHeight();
                            return false;
            }));

            $('#news-search').click(function(event) {
                        jQuery('#news_results').html("Loading...");
                        var query = jQuery("#news-query").val();
                        jQuery.ajax({
                                url: '/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/news1',
                                data: {'query': query},
                                success: function(text) {
                                $('#news_results').html(jQuery(text));
                                },
                                complete: function() {
                        $('.ac_results').hide();
                        $('#news_stories').hide();
                        updateHeight();                                     }
                        });
                    return false; // do not submit the form

            });
            $('#news-form').submit(function(event) {
                        jQuery('#news_results').html("Loading...");
                        var query = jQuery("#news-query").val();
                        jQuery.ajax({
                                url: '/api/upge/cheetah-photo-search/news1',
                                data: {'query': query},
                                success: function(text) {
                                $('#news_results').html(jQuery(text));
                                },
                                complete: function() {
                                $('.ac_results').hide();
                                $('#news_stories').hide();
                                updateHeight();
                                }
                           });
                return false; // do not submit the form

            });
            $('.close_rss').click(ensure(function(){
                $(this).parent().hide('fast');
                $('.news_results').show();
                $('.news_stories').show();
            }));

        });
        // --&gt;
        </script>

            </a>
            in the clear
            <b>
             night
            </b>

            <a class="a_keyword_link" href="http://wn.com/Myanmar" target="_blank">
